title: sweet fruit dressing
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add onion juice.
Add oil, a small amount at a time, alternately with vinegar, the last addition being vinegar.
Use mixer until blended.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken in golden sauce
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Arrange chicken in single layer in buttered shallow baking dish.
Dribble melted butter over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and bake 20 minutes longer.
Stir soups together and pour over chicken.
Bake 20 minutes more.
Cover while baking.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples using a whisk.
Heat, then add apples.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and top with crust. Bake in a 350° oven for approximately 45 minutes or longer.

title: dill bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Stir in 1 cup flour, sour cream, egg, onion, butter, dill seed, dill weed and salt.
Beat by hand until well blended.
Stir in as much remaining flour as can be mixed with spoon.
Turn dough onto a light floured surface; knead in remaining flour to make stiff dough.
Knead 5 to 8 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl.
Turn once to grease surface.
Cover and rise in warm place, 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until double.
Punch down.
Divide in 3 equal pieces.
Cover; let rest 10 minutes.
Roll a piece to 18-inch long rope on floured surface.
Braid ropes loosely from center to ends.
Press rope ends together to seal.
Cover; let rise 30 minutes or double.
Mix egg yolk and 2 tablespoons water and brush on loaf.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or golden and hollow sound.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a large bowl; mix well with electric mixer (until light in color).
Add pecans; stir until evenly coated.
Spread pecans in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 275° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove to waxed paper while still warm, cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yields 8 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
On bottom put Stove Top dressing, chicken, California Blend, cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup.
Add milk.
Put remaining Stove Top on top and salt to taste.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Then add the buttermilk and flavorings.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 325° to 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until brown.
Cool before serving.

title: party bean salad(for a crowd!)
directions: Open can and drain all canned vegetables.
Add onion and celery and mix well. You can add any store-bought oil/vinegar dressing, OR add the following:

title: country-style baked beans casserole
directions: Saute onions and meat; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook on medium-high heat until boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: zucchini michel
directions: In olive oil, saute lightly parsley and onion.
Add tomato sauce, cooking wine, salt, pepper and basil.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Add zucchini, which has been sliced into thin rounds. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and serve.

title: picadillo-cuban cookery
directions: Saute chopped onion, green pepper, garlic and tomato sauce in oil for 5 minutes.
Add ground beef, vinegar, raisins, olives, capers and salt.
Cook, covered, for about 20 minutes; stir occasionally.
Serve with white rice (6 to 8 servings).

title: french apple pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Heap into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Sprinkle with crumb topping.

title: texas punch-bowl cake
directions: Bake cake per directions on box in 2 round layer pans.

In punch bowl, place a layer of strawberries, a layer of cake, (punch holes with handle of wooden spoon), 2-1/2 bananas sliced, 1 box of instant pudding mixed according to directions, second layer of cake, the pineapple, other 2-1/2 bananas sliced, and the other box of pudding (mix as directed).
Let cool in refrigerator. Spread Cool Whip over top, sealing the edges, sprinkle with coconut and pecans.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; beat in sugar and oil.
Stir in zucchini, salt and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to zucchini mixture. Stir in nuts.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken cabbage rotel
directions: Cub cabbage into small pieces and put in large pot.
Add salt and pepper to taste and cook until tender.	Boil or grill chicken. Cut into pieces and place in skillet.
Chop green onions and add to chicken.
Then add all three cans of Ro-Tel (juice included). Also, add the 1 pack of taco seasoning.
Turn on low and simmer until cabbage is done.
Drain cabbage and return to the pot.
Pour chicken mixture on top of cabbage and mix well.
Then pour into a 9 x 13 pan.
Top with sour cream and then add cheese.
Bake at 375° until cheese is melted to golden brown.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown the meat	and
onion
in	a small amount of salad oil. Cook noodles
or elbow mac according to directions.
Put in greased casserole
and
top
with
cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: caramel oatmeal cookies
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix and add oatmeal.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonful on wax paper to cool.

title: rhubarb muffins
directions: Beat first six ingredients.
Sift together flour and soda. Add to first mixture.
At the same time, add the nuts and rhubarb. Mix, just until moist.
Put into 12 muffin tins.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large bowl, stir together the dry ingredients.
Combine the two just until they are mixed well. Turn into an 8 x 8-inch baking pan, well-greased.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lime chiffon salad
directions: Mix jello, water and cream cheese.
Mix well with mixer.
Add nuts and pineapple and set aside to cool.
Whip the cream and add sugar and vanilla.
Fold into jello mixture and chill 2 hours.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients; mix lightly but thoroughly.
Press into an 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour; drain juices.
Let stand 5 minutes; slice and serve.

title: cindy's delight
directions: Put into a large bowl all ingredients and mix well.

title: crunchy cheesy hash browns
directions: Defrost potatoes.
Combine all ingredients except cornflakes and 1/4 cup butter.
Mix cornflakes and 1/4 cup butter; spread on top of potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer vegetables in order given, spread with mayonnaise, sprinkle with cheese and bacon.
Seal and let set for 12 hours.

title: baked coconut shrimp
directions: Combine eggs, lime juice, mustard, curry and salt in a bowl. Dip shrimp into flour, then coat with egg mixture.
Roll in coconut.
Melt butter and pour onto baking sheet.
Bake 5 to 7 minutes in a 350° oven, turning once at 3 to 5 minutes.

title: ambrosia
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate overnight.

title: rice pilaf
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine water, wild rice mix and salt. Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is nearly absorbed.
Stir.
Let stand, covered, for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken in crescent rolls
directions: Combine soup milk, cheese, butter, onion and mushroom in saucepan.
Cook until cheese and butter melt.
Place about 1 tablespoon of chicken in each croissant roll and roll up as directed.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour sauce over rolls.
Top with extra cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: With mixer, on low, mix cocoa with cream, milk and butter in top of double boiler.
When thick, set aside to cool.
Beat egg yolks and pour slowly into chocolate mixture.
Add the sugar-flour mixture and blend well.
Return to heat and cook until quite thick, 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Pour into pre-baked pie shell and cool.

title: strawberry jello pie
directions: Mix apple juice, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan. Cook on medium heat 2 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add gelatin. Stir 2 minutes until dissolved. Place strawberries cut in half in pie crust. Pour gelatin mixture over strawberries. Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm. Cool Whip can be placed on top before serving.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add garlic and cook 2 minutes. Add onion and cook until soft.
Add clams, juice, red pepper, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes. Meanwhile, cook 1 pound linguine in large pot of boiling salted water.
Drain, when done, and place linguine in a large serving dish.
Pour hot sauce over linguine.
Sprinkle with cheese (and parsley, if desired) and serve immediately.

title: premium turkey salad
directions: Drain turkey breast.
Place in a medium mixing bowl and flake. Add Miracle Whip to turkey.
Sprinkle in salt and garlic powder. Add diced celery.
Mix well and serve on sandwich buns or with crackers.

title: neiman-marcus brownies
directions: Mix together and press in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: quick and hearty baked bean soup
directions: Combine all of the ingredients except mustard.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Puree mixture 1/3 at a time.
(Note: This step may be omitted for "chunky style" soup.)
Add mustard and heat through.
Makes 2 quarts in a little over 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg whites, peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Pour butter in baking dish.
Sift flour, sugar and baking powder and beat together.
Add milk and mix.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Spread peaches and 1/2 of juice on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wild persimmon pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash the persimmons under cold running water.

Remove the seeds and set aside for 20 minutes. Mash the persimmons through a colander or strainer to make a pulp. (If the persimmons are very nice, you can just remove the seeds and put the persimmons in a blender to process.)
Beat the eggs, adding the sugar, until well mixed.
Add the milk, alternating with the flour, in thirds, combining well.
Add the vanilla and cinnamon.
Stir in the persimmons (and raisins and walnuts, if used).
Mix well.
Melt the butter in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish or 9 x 12-inch pan and tilt the pan to coat the bottom and sides with butter.
Pour the persimmon mixture into the pan.
Bake for 1 hour or until firm.
Serve with whipped topping.
Serves 6.

title: spicy chili
directions: Brown beef; drain.
Add onion, garlic, tomatoes and seasonings; cook until onion is tender.
Stir in the remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: slow-cooked oriental chicken
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, brown the chicken in oil on both sides.
Transfer to a slow cooker.
Combine the soy sauce, brown sugar, water, garlic and ginger; pour over chicken.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour.
Reduce heat to low; cook 4 to 5 hours longer or until the meat juices run clear.
Remove chicken to a serving platter; sprinkle with slivered almonds for an Oriental touch!
Spoon juices over chicken or thicken if desired. Yield: 4 to 5 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Bake approximately 1 hour.
Cream eggs, oil and vanilla together.
Add all dry ingredients.
Mix well. Stir in zucchini and nuts.
Pour into 2 well-greased loaf pans or 1 Bundt pan.
Bake until knife comes out clean.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados; add garlic salt and salt and pepper to taste. Add lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Add onion and picante sauce to taste.
Mix all together until smooth.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring sugar, milk and butter to a boil; boil for 3 minutes. Take off stove and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat with a spoon.
Pour into a greased pan and let set. Cut into squares.

title: sour cream banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk together until it starts to thicken.
Add sour cream and a little less than half container of Cool Whip (reserve remaining half for topping).
Make layers, beginning with wafers, then bananas, then pudding mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with crushed wafers.
Yields 20 to 24 servings.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Scald milk, pour over cornmeal; let cook to lukewarm.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well greased 9 inch baking pan.
Bake in a 425 degree oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: brazil nut cookies
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, nuts and vanilla, then work in flour.
Work dough with hands to bring out the oil of the nuts.
Form in 5 or 6 rolls; refrigerate overnight.
Cut cookies about 1/4-inch thick or less.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes on greased cookie sheets.

title: potato supreme casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk. In greased 9 x 13 baking dish, layer alternating potatoes, onions, cheese, salt and pepper. Pour sauce over top.
Dot with butter. Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour. Uncover and bake 15 minutes until browned and potatoes are soft.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, beat butter, both sugars and vanilla until light and fluffy. Add eggs and beat well. Gradually add flour mixture, beating well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to
11 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool slightly.
Remove from cookie sheet to wire rack. Cool completely. Makes 6 dozen cookies.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cook beef in nonstick skillet and stir to crumble.
Stir meat into first mixture and simmer 25 to 30 minutes.

title: favorite spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain.
Add bell pepper, onion, salt, garlic powder, sugar, and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to a simmer and cook 2-3 hours.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: orange julius
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and serve cold.

title: cheese balls
directions: In a bowl, beat the egg yolks with a wire whisk until light colored.
Stir in the milk, then gradually add the flour and beat until smooth.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold the yolk mixture into the whites, adding the salt, pepper, nutmeg, cheeses, ham and onion.
Drop by teaspoonful into hot oil, at least 1/2-inch deep and fry, turning once, until just golden.
Do not overcook.
Drain and serve immediately or keep warm in a 250° oven for up to 1 hour.

title: hot pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix warm water, yeast and sugar.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Mix salt and flour in a large bowl.
Add yeast mixture.
Work the dough into shapes on a flour-covered counter or pastry cloth.
Put on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Beat egg and brush on pretzels.
Sprinkle on salt, if desired.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Best when eaten warm.
Makes 8 to 10 large pretzels.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Stir together all ingredients.
Sprinkle top with sugar.
Put into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs, honey and baking soda thoroughly. Stir in remaining ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown.
Cool 2 to 3 minutes before removing from cookie sheet.

title: pork chops and mushroom gravy
directions: Sprinkle pork
chops
with lemon pepper.
Brown on both sides and place in a baking dish.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Make small meatballs out of ground beef; put broth, tortellini and spinach on stove.
Add meatballs, cook until tortellini are tender, about 20 minutes.
Serve with grated cheese and Italian bread.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Slice beef into bite-sized strips.
Cook broccoli and carrots in boiling salted water, covered, for 2 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, salt, sugar, soy sauce and sherry.
Set aside.
Stir-fry broccoli, carrots and onions in hot oil for 2 minutes.
Remove from wok. Add 1/2 the beef to wok; fry for 2 minutes.
Remove beef; stir-fry remaining beef.
Return all beef to wok.
Add peas, water chestnuts and bamboo shoots.
Add soy mixture to wok.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Return broccoli, carrots and onion to wok; cover and cook 1 minute.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: Cook carrots in small amount of water until barely tender. Drain and cool. Slice onion thin and cut bell pepper in strips. Combine with carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over carrot mixture.

title: oreo cookie cake(delicious and rich)
directions: Mix 20 cookies and butter.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 9x13-inch pan according to box directions. Let cool.

title: peaches 'n cream cheesecake
directions: Combine first seven ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch pan.
Place peaches over batter in pan.
Combine cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and reserved juice in small bowl.
Beat at medium speed.
Combine last 2 ingredients and sprinkle over.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, onions, peppers and celery.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook over moderate heat 45 minutes.
Seal in jars.

title: baked corn
directions: Place corn in greased baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and pepper with corn.
Stir in milk and well beaten eggs.
Pour melted butter over top, but do not stir in.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake in moderate, 350°, oven until brown and center is firm.

title: easy caramel-pecan rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix pecans, brown sugar, corn syrup and 1/4 cup butter in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Spread to cover bottom of pan.
Set aside.

title: sauce pot meatballs
directions: In a deep thick saucepan, quickly bring to a boil soup mix, water and 3/4 can of tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Mix ground beef, seasonings, parsley and remaining 1/4 can tomato sauce.
Shape into 16 meatballs and place in sauce.
Simmer gently, uncovered, for 25 minutes, turning occasionally.
Serve over hot noodles or spaghetti.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg and cheese casserole
directions: Melt butter over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Remove from heat and gradually stir in milk.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly until thick and smooth.
Add cheese, stirring until melted.
Add pimento and eggs.
Turn into a greased 1 1/2 qt. baking dish and top with scalloped crackers.
Bake at 350° 20-25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings

title: no cook fruit cake
directions: Put margarine and marshmallows in double boiler and melt.
Add fruit and raisins; mix well.
Add nuts and
stir.
Add crushed graham crackers and mix well.
Pack firmly in pan.
Leave for 24 hours before cutting.

title: hot cocoa
directions: In medium saucepan combine sugar, cocoa and salt; blend in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils.
Boil and stir 2 minutes.
Add milk; stir and heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla. Beat with rotary beater or wire whisk until foamy.
Serve hot, topped with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes about 6 (6 ounce) servings.

title: crispy sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers about 1/8-inch thick.
Dissolve lime in water and cover cucumber slices.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Rinse well. Let stand for 3 hours in clear water; drain.
Mix well the vinegar, sugar, cloves and salt and pour over cucumbers.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, bring to a boil for 35 to 40 minutes.
Fill sterilized jars within 1/2-inch of top with cucumbers and syrup.
Put on cap; screw band firmly tight. Process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Yields 10 pints.

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend ingredients and chill about 20 minutes. Form into 1 or 2 balls and roll into nuts.
Best if left overnight before serving.

title: garlic pickles
directions: Slice pickles into 1/4-inch slices.
Layer pickles in pint jar to 1 1/2-inch layer.
Cut garlic over pickles (3 small).
Sprinkle 5 tablespoons sugar over pickles.
Continue layers until jar is full.
Pour vinegar over all.
Refrigerate.
Shake jar often. Ready to eat third day.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburg and bacon together.
Cook onions and green pepper together until tender.
Drain off excess liquid; add catsup, salt, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, garlic powder, kidney beans and butter beans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: celebration chicken buns
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet on medium heat. Add green pepper, celery, onion and garlic.
Saute until crisp-tender. Add ketchup, Worcestershire sauce, vinegar, brown sugar, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Mix well.
Heat to a boil. Reduce heat. Stir in chicken. Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon 1/4 cup chicken mixture over bottom half of each bun. Replace top.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken-vegetable luncheon salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain. Rinse with cool water to cool quickly and drain well. Combine chicken and veggies with pasta in large bowl. Add dressing; toss lightly. Chill at least 2 hours, tossing occasionally. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: deep dish peach crumble
directions: In a 10 x 6-inch baking dish, combine peaches, sugar, tapioca, lemon juice and salt.
In small bowl, blend together into coarse crumbs the flour, brown sugar and margarine.
Pat uniformly over the top of fruit.
Cover and bake 15 minutes in a 375° oven. Remove cover; bake 30 to 40 minutes more until peaches are soft and brown across top.
Delicious warm or cold.

title: broccoli cheese sauce
directions: Combine soup and milk.
Conventional:
Heat over medium heat until hot and bubbling, stirring often.
Microwave:
Microwave uncovered on High 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring halfway through heating.
Serve over vegetables such as broccoli, cauliflower and carrots, etc.

title: olive-nut sandwich
directions: Let cream cheese stand at room temperature until soft.
Mash with a fork and add the mayonnaise.
Chop up pecans and salad olives.
Put in a bowl and add olive juice with a dash of pepper (no salt).
Stir well; this will be mush.
It's supposed to be that way!
Put in a pint fruit jar and refrigerate for at least 24 to 48 hours.
It will be thick.
Spread on bread.
Can use black walnuts or any other kind of nuts.

title: baked spareribs aloha
directions: Bake ribs about 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Drain off fat.
Add rest of ingredients and bake about 40 minutes.
Baste often.

title: grandma frazier's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Combine flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
Add them alternately with the sour milk.
Stir in oats and raisins or gumdrops.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal candy
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oatmeal, and boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in 2 1/2 cups of 1-minute oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on buttered wax paper.

title: crunchy cauliflower salad
directions: Mix cauliflower, water chestnuts, onions and radishes.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and buttermilk dressing mix. Mix dressing with vegetables.
Chill.

title: cherry pie
directions: Combine juice, sugar, tapioca, salt and cherries; let stand about 15 minutes.
Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Fill with cherry mixture.
Dot with butter.
Adjust top crust.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: raisin bars
directions: Put 4 graham crackers in a plastic bag.
Press bag flat.
Tie it closed.
Whack the crackers with big spoon until they are tiny crumbs.
Put the crumbs in a large bowl.
Whack all the crackers into crumbs.
Open can of sweetened condensed milk; put the milk in the bowl.
Put the raisins in the bowl; mix with big spoon.
Add cereal to the bowl; mix.
It will be stiff.
You may have to use your hands.
Spread some butter all over the inside of the baking pan.
Put the mixture in the pan.
Press it down with your fingers. Let the pan sit for 15 minutes.
Cut the mixture into 16 bar cookies.

title: gooey butter cookies
directions: Beat the butter, cream cheese, egg and vanilla in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy. Stir in the dry cake mix. Chill, covered, for 30 minutes. Drop the dough by teaspoonfuls into a bowl of confectioners sugar and roll into balls. Arrange on cookie sheets lightly coated with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Cool on wire racks. Makes 3 dozen.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix together with wire whisk and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until filling is set.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix together flour, chopped nuts and margarine.
Pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish (ungreased).
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hunter stew
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots together.
Brown sausage and onion; add meats (except shrimp), vegetables and seasonings.
Cook slowly about 1 1/2 hours.
Add shrimp last 5 minutes of cooking time. Serve over rice with barbecue bread and green salad.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix water and yeast together.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 3 tablespoons salad oil, salt and 4 2/3 cups flour.
Mix until all flour is moist.
Add remaining flour until smooth (takes about 10 minutes).
Place in large bowl and brush with salad oil.
Cover and place in a warm place for 2 hours.

title: fresh banana eggnog
directions: Peel and mash bananas.
Add egg and sugar; blend until smooth and well combined.
Add milk and vanilla; continue to mix until just combined.

title: hobo dinners
directions: In center of large square of heavy-duty aluminum foil, place 1/2 pound patty of ground chuck, shaped into a patty.
Place thick slice of onion on meat.
Place large chunks of potato and carrots on top, then mushrooms, green pepper or other choice of fresh vegetables.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Wrap in foil and cook over hot coals 1 hour, flipping occasionally, until done. Makes 4 large portions.

title: tea cakes
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat well.
Add vanilla, then stir in flour.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 275°. Cook until lightly brown.

title: pork chop potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in thin slices.
Place potatoes in greased baking dish in 3 layers, 1-inch deep, sprinkling each layer with salt, pepper and flour and dotting with butter.
Add milk until it can be seen between slices of potatoes but not to cover.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours uncovered.

title: 7-up cake *
directions: Cream together.
Pour into a well-greased pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: Put milk on stove and slowly bring to a boil.
Beat eggs and add sugar and flour.
After milk comes to a boil, add pudding mixture to milk.
Stir continuously until pudding gets thick. Take mixture off fire and add vanilla and pat of butter.
Stir pudding until butter melts.
Layer bananas on bottom of bowl. Pour half pudding mix over them, then a layer of vanilla wafers. Pour mixture over all.
Top with vanilla wafers.

title: banana burritos
directions: Peel and cut bananas in half lengthwise.
Brush with lime juice.
Set aside.
In dry medium skillet, soften tortillas one at a time over medium heat, by turning over 2 to 3 times until warm and limp.
Keep warm.
Spread 1 tablespoon apricot preserves over each tortilla.
Place a banana half across lower third of tortilla.
Sprinkle with cinnamon; roll up.
Lay seam side down on plate.
In heavy skillet, heat oil and butter over medium heat. Put tortillas in hot oil.
Brown lightly.
Serve with dollop of whipped cream and nuts or berries.
Serves 4.

title: boiled custard
directions: Pour
milk
into a large container.
Set this container in a pan
of
water
to	make
a double boiler.	Heat milk to lukewarm. Beat
egg yolks well; add sugar and stir.	Add some of the
warm milk to egg mixture and mix well.
Pour into the milk.
Stir constantly	until
mixture	coats a spoon.	Cool. Add vanilla.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients together until well blended. Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Cut up apples or use strawberries whole and dip into cream dip.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Mix sugar, salt, dry mustard, Tabasco, ketchup, vinegar and salad oil together.
Soak thin slices of white onions in ice water while boiling green shrimp.
Place a layer of onion, layer of shrimp and layer of bay leaves.
Pour sauce over (continue in layers).
Use wide-mouth jar to store.
Refrigerate; will keep indefinitely.

title: old-fashion potato candy
directions: Wash potato; boil potato with skin until soft.
Peel potato and mash in large mixing bowl.
Add powdered sugar.
Mix until it's like biscuit dough, then roll the dough like you would a pizza.
Spread peanut butter with a knife until completely covered.
Start at one end and roll the dough up.
Refrigerate. Cut into pieces and serve.

title: christmas cutouts(sugar cookies)
directions: Cream the butter; add sugar gradually, creaming all the while. Add well beaten eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Sift the flour with baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Add to first mixture gradually, stirring in.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Roll out on lightly floured board very thin (1/8 inch or less).
Cut in shapes.
Bake in 350° oven until light brown, 10 minutes.

title: creamy dill dip
directions: Thoroughly combine sour cream, mayonnaise, onion, dill weed and seasoned salt.
Cover and chill thoroughly to blend flavors. Makes 2 cups.

title: veal and peppers(italian style)
directions: Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Brown on all sides in hot oil in skillet.
Add peppers.
Cover and reduce heat.
Cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add mushrooms and liquid, red pepper and sauce.
Cover and simmer until tender, 30 minutes longer.
Season to taste.
Serve on hot cooked rice, macaroni or spaghetti.

title: beet relish
directions: Mix ingredients.
Cover with vinegar.
Heat mixture to the boiling point.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: sweet and sour cucumbers
directions: Prepare 1 hour or more before serving. In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in 2 (4-quart) slow cookers (this is a very large recipe). Cover. Cook on low 10 to 11 hours.

title: southern potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets until tender; peel and slice thinly. Combine remaining ingredients except pimento.
Mix until well blended.
Place a layer of sliced potatoes in casserole, then add a layer of sour cream mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with sour cream mixture.
Garnish with pimento.
May be served warm or cold

title: apricot chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Pour mixture over.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Take cover off and bake 15 minutes longer in 350° oven.
Good with rice and salad.

title: whoopee pies
directions: Cream sugar, Spry and vanilla.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients with sour milk.
Make paste with cocoa and water.
Drop by tablespoons.
Bake in 375° oven.

title: ginger's baked potato in a bowl
directions: Peel and chop approximately 12 potatoes. Put them in a large pot with enough water to barely cover them.
Do not put too much water in the pot.

Chop green onions. Add 2 teaspoons of salt and pepper. If available, add 1 teaspoon of garlic powder. Add half of the green onions. Bring to a boil. Cook the bacon until crisp and chop. Reduce heat to medium and mash potatoes in pot once they are soft.
Add butter, 1 cup milk and 8 ounces sour cream and stir.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix
ingredients
together
well, in a saucepan and heat thoroughly.
Salt
and pepper meat you wish to barbecue.
Place meat in
a	casserole dish and pour the sauce over it.
Bake at 325° until meat is tender and done.

title: paper bag barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Mix well.
Dip chicken in sauce.
Place in brown paper bag. Pour rest of sauce over it.
Put in another bag; fold tight and place in covered pan.
Cook 15 minutes at 450°.
Turn to 350° and cook 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: texas meatballs
directions: Mix beef, sausage, bread crumbs and egg. Shape into balls. Brown meatballs.
Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients except rice. Cover and cook over low heat 20 minutes until done. Stir occasionally. Serve over rice.
Makes 5 cups.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown onion, garlic and mushrooms in butter.
Add meat and brown.
Add liquids, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add uncooked noodles; cover and cook until tender, about 7 minutes. Add sour cream; stir gently.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Serves 4. Freezes well.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip in shallow platter.
Mash avocados and mix in lemon juice and garlic salt.
Spread avocado mixture on top of bean dip.
Mix taco seasoning into sour cream and spread on top of avocado layer.
Top with a layer of tomatoes and olives.
Spread grated cheese on top and sprinkle with green onions.

title: baked apples with pineapple filling
directions: Core apples and score around the center.
Place apples in a shallow ovenproof dish.
Add about 1/2-inch water or white wine. Stir together pineapple and raisins.
Divide the filling between the apples.
Pour 2 tablespoons of the melted jelly over each apple.
Place in an oven preheated to 350° and bake until the apples are tender, about 30 to 60 minutes.
Baste from time to time as the apples are cooking. When baked, place the apples in small dishes and spoon over any liquid that is in the pan.
Chill.

title: low calorie strawberry pie
directions: Mix and heat water and cornstarch until thickened.
While hot, add gelatin.
Mix well.
Let cool and add sweetener and strawberries.
Mix well and pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill before serving.
Pie may be topped with light whipped topping.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Drain green beans.
In large casserole dish, place one layer of green beans and one layer of corn.
Repeat.
Make at least two layers of each.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix well all ingredients and cook 2 hours at 350°.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes
until tender.
Peel, cool and cube half. Combine potatoes,
green onions and pimiento in bowl.
Combine mayonnaise and
all other ingredients.
Stir into potatoes and toss gently.
Cover and chill.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken and take off bone.
Then put chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle with pepper and/or poultry seasoning. Put onions and potatoes on top of chicken.
Mix both soups and broth together and pour over vegetables and chicken.
Do not stir. Mix flour, baking powder, margarine (melted) and milk together. Pour over top.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: pine cone cheese spread
directions: Spread almonds in single layer in a shallow pan and bake at 300 degrees about 15 minutes, stirring often (until they begin to turn color)

title: boiled cookies
directions: Put sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a pan; bring to a boil. Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from fire and beat in oatmeal, peanut butter, vanilla and nuts quickly.
Drop a teaspoon at a time on waxed paper and let stand until cool.

title: tamales and corn masa dough
directions: Fry meat in oil.
Add the other ingredients.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.

title: sunday surprise cake
directions: Grease and flour 8-inch square pan.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Stir in egg.
Add flour and milk alternately, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Pour in pan and spread with preserves.
Combine 1/4 cup flour, sugar, cinnamon and butter. Sprinkle over preserves.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven. Cut in squares and serve warm.

title: terry's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Use electric mixer to mix all.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
At the end, add walnuts and chips.

title: fruit pie
directions: Melt butter in a deep pan.
Mix flour, 1 cup sugar, milk, baking powder and salt.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir. Mix fruit and 1 cup sugar.
Pour over batter, but do not stir. Bake at 350° to 375° until done.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Bring water, salt, sugar and vinegar to a boil.
Put fish in and cook for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove fish from water, top with butter and put in broiler for about 5 minutes.
Serve with butter and lemon juice.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix together butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla thoroughly.
Sift together and stir in flour and salt.
Mix in chopped nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake until set but not brown.
While still warm, roll in confectioners sugar.
When cool, do it again.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: ham and cheese pinwheels
directions: Filling:
Combine cream cheese, ham, Cheddar cheese, onion, parsley and mustard.
Mix well.

title: baby food cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes (thin Bundt pan) or 1 hour (thick Bundt pan).

title: mulled cider
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all.
Bring to boil; reduce to low.
Simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Strain and serve hot.

title: amaretto cheesecake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients to make crust. Beat the cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually add 1 cup sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Stir in 1/3 cup Amaretto.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: pickle relish
directions: Grind the first 4 ingredients.
Add the salt.
Let stand 2 hours.
Drain real dry.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Let stand 1 week (or) bring to a boil and seal.
Good on hot dogs or with beans, fried potatoes and corn bread.

title: meat and potatoes
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Place layer of meat in casserole, layer of potatoes, onion and celery.
Season, then add 1/2 can of soup.
Repeat layers.
Pour hot water over top and cover casserole.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Fry ground beef; drain and place in casserole dish.
Place layer of potato rounds on top of this, then a layer of cheese and onions.
Repeat procedure until dish is full.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Cook in 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes through potatoes easily.

title: fresh cucumbers
directions: Layer cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle salt on each layer. Cover and put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Pour this liquid off.

title: hot brown
directions: Cut toast into squares.
Layer bottom of 1 1/2-quart dish with toast.
Top with pieces of chicken.
Mix soup and water until warm.
Add cheese and mushrooms. Pour on top of chicken. Put crumbled bacon on top; add cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken wild rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Debone, chop and set aside.
Spoon cooked rice into lightly greased casserole.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Bake cake by package directions.
Melt shortening in bottom of pan.
Add brown sugar and spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Place pineapple slices over mixture.
Place a cherry in center of each pineapple slice.
Pour cake over sugar and pineapple and bake. Heat pineapple juice, water, butter and sugar.
Pour over cake when its baked and still hot.
Poke holes in it with fork to soak up pineapple juice mixture.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Greased
8 x 8 x 2-inch square pan. Place apple
slices
in
pan.
Mix
remaining
ingredients. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes until apples are tender and top is golden
brown.
Serve
warm
and, if desired, with light cream or ice cream.

title: french toast
directions: Mix all ingredients together and dip bread into egg butter. Cook in skillet dotted with butter until done on both sides. Before serving, sprinkle powdered sugar on toast.

title: cake frosting
directions: Use large mixing bowl for electric mixer.
Mix the first 3 ingredients by hand.
Add water and mix with electric mixer until water is absorbed.
Add flavoring and vinegar and mix.
Beat with mixer, slowly adding the powdered sugar.

title: pralines
directions: Cook sugar, salt and milk until it comes to a rolling boil. Add butter.
Let it remain on fire until butter has completely melted.
Remove from fire and beat for a few minutes until it begins to thicken. Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
If it gets too hard to drop, return to fire and re-melt.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine 1 stick oleo and graham cracker crumbs and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat sugar, eggs and butter 15 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Add layer bananas, layer of pineapple and layer of Cool Whip and add nuts and cherries.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: gold corn bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl; add egg, milk and shortening. Beat with eggbeater until smooth; place in pans (8-inch), greased. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook the potatoes until done. Saute the onions and melted butter. Add the salt, flour and pepper. Stir and cook until smooth and bubbly. Add the milk. Stir over medium heat until thick. Combine the potatoes and potato water. Add to sauce. Heat and serve.

title: homemade waffles
directions: Mix ingredients in blender and refrigerate about 1 hour before cooking.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown the hamburger meat; drain.
Combine about 5 cups of water with the meat in a stew pot.
Add the bouillon cubes.
Add the carrots.
After about 10 to 15 minutes, add the potatoes. Cook until the carrots and potatoes are about done.
Add the cabbage; let it cook for awhile.
Add the corn, beans, mushrooms and salt and pepper.
You can also put noodles.
These need to be added about the same time as the potatoes and cabbage.
Let it cook for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Layer macaroni and vegetables.
Pour soup mixture over each layer.
Put shredded cheese on top of each layer.
Can cook peas and carrots before laying.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and soup mixture is set.
Makes 12 servings.

title: quick and easy stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into small strips. Brown round steak in oil. Add diced onions and salt and pepper to taste. Drain oil. Add cream of mushroom and cream of chicken soup, cream cheese and sour cream. Reduce heat. Simmer. Add mushrooms. Stir occasionally for approximately 15 minutes or until ingredients are well blended. Cook egg noodles as directed on package. Pour stroganoff over noodles and serve.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover and chill.

title: studenina(jellied pigs feet)
directions: Wash meat thoroughly.
Place in a large kettle and cover with water.
Bring to boiling point and skim.
Add onion, celery, bay leaves, peppercorns and salt to taste.
Simmer slowly, covered, for about 3 or 4 hours or until meat comes off bones easily.
Cool slightly.
Remove bones from meat.
Mash garlic into a little salt and mix into the liquid.
Return meat to liquid and pour into Pyrex dishes or any serving dish.
Set in refrigerator until firm.

title: grilled parmesan potatoes
directions: Place cast-iron skillet on grill.
Melt margarine or butter in skillet on low heat.
Combine next 5 ingredients in small bowl. Dampen potato halves in water; toss in dry mixture.
Place in cast-iron skillet.
Cook with cover down on medium setting for 35 minutes or until done, turning once.

title: variegated rice salad
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions and chill.
Layer red cabbage, beans, eggs and rice in a large glass bowl. Repeat with remaining vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Spread over top.
Loosely cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Yields 12 servings, 127 calories per serving.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add vinegar.
Let sauce boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add butter.
Pour sauce over beets. Let simmer 30 minutes.

title: dorito dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on the bottom of a 10-inch Pyrex pie plate.
Then, in order, layer the next 4 ingredients on top of the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (or microwave for 7 to 9 minutes).
Dip Doritos in the hot dip.

title: tabouli
directions: Combine bulgur and boiling water in a medium to large bowl. Cover and let stand until the bulgur is tender (20 to 30 minutes, minimum).
Add salt, lemon juice, garlic and black pepper and mix thoroughly.
Cover tightly and refrigerate until about 30 minutes before serving.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add all other ingredients. Simmer in a large saucepan at least 45 minutes.

title: fast goodies
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well. Spoon into tiny greased muffin pans, filling 1/2 full. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done. Makes 4 dozen.

title: percolator punch
directions: Pour all liquid ingredients into bottom of 12-cup electric percolator.
Put all spices and sugar into basket of percolator. Perk as you would coffee.
Makes 10 cups.

title: bacon and egg casserole
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain on paper towel and crumble. Spray a 9 x 10 x 2-inch casserole dish with vegetable spray.
Place croutons in casserole and pour margarine over them.
Sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Mix milk, eggs and mustard and pour over cheese.
Sprinkle bacon crumbs over all.
Bake at 325 for 45 minutes.
Allow casserole to stand 15 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: hot fruit
directions: Combine sugar and butter. Set aside. Layer fruit and nuts in a 2-quart casserole dish. Pour butter mixture over fruit. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Remove from oven and let cool.

title: tex-mex bean dip
directions: Peel, core, and quarter apples.
Cook with enough water to keep apples from sticking to pan.
Drain off excess juice.
Put through colander or ricer and measure 9 cups pulp.
To the pulp add 1/2 cup vinegar, 5 cups sugar, 1/4 cup cinnamon.
Cook in 300° oven for 2 to 3 hours until mixture becomes quite thick.
Stir occasionally. Put into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: strawberry punch
directions: In a 6-quart container, mix together first 7 ingredients. Loosely cover and freeze until firm.
tags: unsweetened cherry flavor soft drink mix

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heavily grease and flour a 12-cup fluted tube pan. Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Stir until just blended. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool 15 minutes in pan. Turn onto rack to cool completely. Serves 12 to 16.

title: chess pie
directions: Butter should be at room temperature.
Mix first 4 ingredients real good; add to butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla; mix well.
Put in a 9-inch deep dish pie crust.
Cook until done.

title: old fashioned coffee cake("the best")
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend butter and sugar in large bowl (use pastry cutter to blend).
Add vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well after each addition. Blend in sour cream.
Add dry ingredients gradually; beat until well blended.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture into well-greased 10-inch tube pan.
Mix nuts, cinnamon and 2 tablespoons sugar; sprinkle 1/2 of this into batter.
Add rest of batter; top with rest of nut mixture.
Cut through with knife to marble slightly.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Turn out of pan.
Dissolve brown sugar in orange juice (warm over low heat).
Brush this mixture over top and sides of warm cake. Incredible!

title: peanut butter and chocolate crispy squares
directions: Heat marshmallow and peanut butter in large saucepan over low heat until melted and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat immediately.
Add cereal.
Mix lightly until well coated.
Press into greased 13x9x2 inch pan.
Cool completely.
Cut into squares.

title: oreo dirt
directions: Soften and mix together the oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Beat together the pudding and milk.
Mix the two mixtures together.
Fold into pudding mixture the Cool Whip.
Crush cookies.
Layer Oreos, pudding and Oreos.
Make sure you cover top with Oreos.
You may stick a flower in it for decorations.

title: berniece camp's rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to directions on package, omitting butter. Cool. Toss chopped onions, pepper and olives. Drain artichokes, reserving marinade. Add marinade to mayonnaise and stir into all other ingredients, except artichokes.
Coarsely chop artichokes and add last. Salad can be refrigerated and kept for as long as 3 days.

title: cattlemen's ribs and beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim excess fat from ribs.
In a small bowl, combine salt, pepper, oregano, basil and chili powder.
Mix well.
Rub seasonings into ribs, covering all sides.
Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a medium skillet.
Brown ribs in oil until golden brown on all sides.
Remove ribs and set aside.
Add remaining oil, if needed.
Saute onions and garlic in oil until onion softens.
Cover bottom of a shallow 4-quart casserole with sauteed onion mixture.
Place ribs on top of onion.
Pour in wine. Cover and bake until ribs are fork-tender, 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add beans.
Cover and bake 30 minutes.
Remove ribs and place on a warmed platter.
Stir beans into pan juices before serving around ribs.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
When cool, peel, slice and set aside.
Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Stir in vinegar and water. Cook until clear.
Add bacon, salt, pepper and a little onion to taste.
Pour over potatoes (more bacon drippings can be added for more taste).
Recipe can be tripled and placed in a crock-pot for a "crowd pleaser" or heated in oven until warm.

title: quick vegetable soup
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add V-8 juice, soup mix and mixed vegetables.
Cook until thickened (as desired).

title: potato kielbasa casserole
directions: In saucepan melt margarine and stir in flour.
Cook the roux, stirring for a minute, then gradually add milk, stirring until the sauce begins to thicken.
Stir in salt and pepper and set aside. Grease 3-quart casserole.
Spread 1/3 of the potato slices on the bottom, then 1/2 of the onions, followed by 1/2 of the cabbage and 1/2 of the kielbasa in layers over potatoes.
Add 1/3 of the sauce. Repeat the layers, ending with potatoes.
Add the rest of the sauce.
Cover the casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: microwave buttered fish fillets
directions: Place fish in single layer in microwave-safe dish.
Cover with vented wrap (plastic).
Microcook on High for 4 to 7 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with fork.
Using a slotted spoon, transfer fish to serving platter.
Place margarine in a 1 cup microwave-safe measure.
Cook on High for 40 seconds to 1 1/2 minutes or until melted.
Stir in juice and herb.
Drizzle over fish.
Garnish fish with lemon or lime peel or sprig of fresh herbs.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased pie pan (makes its own crust).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato salad
directions: In large bowl, stir together mayonnaise and all other ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover; refrigerate for at least 2 1/2 hours; if desired, sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 8 cups.

title: chewy squares
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan over low heat and add sugar. Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well with large wooden spoon.
Add flour, vanilla, butternut flavoring, coconut flakes and pecans.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Pour in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: fried "louisiana" oysters
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients, except oysters and cooking oil. Roll oysters in mix.
So that mixture sticks to oysters, do not fry for about 4 minutes.
Deep fry in hot oil until brown.

title: egg casserole or breakfast brunch
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, roll out crescent rolls so that they are flat on the bottom and come up about halfway on the sides of baking pan.
Add bacon and cheese.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs and milk together.
Pour over bacon and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: dry marinade for spareribs
directions: Combine sugar, paprika, salt and pepper in small bowl.
Pat ribs dry with paper toweling.
Rub ribs with garlic.
Rub with dry mixture.
Let stand 1 hour at room temperature.
Wrap ribs in heavy-duty foil packet.
Ribs can be cooked on grill or in oven. Baste with favorite barbecue sauce when ribs are done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash.
Grate cheese.
In a large bowl, mix squash, cheese, salt to taste, pepper to taste and slightly beaten egg. Put in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° to 400°.

title: ranch-style meal
directions: Cook ground beef with onions, stirring to crumble meat. When done,
drain
fat
and
add rest of ingredients.
Simmer, covered, about 10 minutes.
Serve with Mexican Cornbread.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and put 1 pound crumbled bacon on top.
Return to oven and bake for 10 more minutes.
(I use bacon bits.)

title: two tone cheese cake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter together.
Press in bottom of spring-form pan.

title: delicious cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by spoonfuls into powdered sugar and roll into balls.
Bake in ungreased pan for 9 to 12 minutes.
Do not overcook.

title: old time egg custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Grease baking dish with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° until mixture is solid.

title: broiled herbed lamb chops
directions: Place broiler pan under hot broiler to heat.
Mince garlic with salt to form paste.
Place in cup; add oil and seasonings. Mix.
Spread over chops.
Place chops in broiler pan.
Broil 4-inches from heat source, 2 minutes on each side or until medium-rare.
Makes 4 servings.

title: barbecups
directions: Brown ground beef and drain. Add barbecue sauce, onion and brown sugar. Press each biscuit into a muffin cup, making sure dough goes up to the edge of cup. Spoon meat on top and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: yummy bundt cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, pudding, olive oil, and egg with electric mixer.
While mixing, slowly pour in the very hot tap water and vanilla.
Fold in chocolate chips.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown beef, onions and peppers.
Combine meal, corn, milk, eggs, baking soda and baking fat in a large bowl.
Pour half of batter in greased skillet or baking pan.
Spoon meat mixture evenly over batter.
Sprinkle with half of the cheese.
Top with remaining batter.
Sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Bake in oven 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger or ground turkey and season with picante sauce.
Add beans to meat and set aside to cool.
Combine lettuce, onion, tomatoes, avocado and cheese.
Before serving, add meat, chips and dressing and toss.

title: chocolate pudding parfait
directions: Combine cocoa and cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir constantly. Remove from heat.

title: old-fashioned macaroni and cheese
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook macaroni.
Place half the macaroni in ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with half the onion, salt, pepper and cheese.
Repeat.
Pour white sauce over casserole.
Dot with butter. Cover and bake for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread pie filling in bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine dry cake mix, nuts and melted butter (mixture will be crumbly).
Sprinkle mixture over pie filling.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Refrigerate first 4 ingredients overnight (in the cans). Mix all ingredients the next morning.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Bake together almonds and sesame seed at 350° until brown. Cool.
Add cabbage and noodles.
Just before serving, add the dressing.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Combine sugars and milk.
Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Add butter, pecans and vanilla.
Mix completely and then do not stir anymore.
Cook until temperature reaches 238° (soft-ball stage).
Cool almost 3 minutes.
Beat until thickened. Pour out onto a well-greased surface and allow to harden.

title: grandma's caramel corn
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda and vanilla. Pour over popcorn.
Mix.
Put mixture into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 250° mixing every 15 minutes.

title: green bean salad
directions: Rinse beans in cold water and drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar and oil and pour over beans.
Add garlic salt, pepper and oregano. Toss and chill overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: french beef stew
directions: Dissolve bouillon in the boiling water.
Place beef, potatoes, carrots, mushrooms and onions in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole. Sprinkle with crumbled bread and tapioca.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour bouillon over all.
Cover tightly with foil.

title: waldorf cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add flour mixture to Crisco-sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and red food color; beat well.
Fold in soda, dissolved in vinegar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Put sugar, salt, butter and syrup in bowl and microwave for 2 minutes.
Take out and stir.
Put back in microwave for 2 more minutes.
Take out.
Add baking soda and stir until it changes color and almost doubles in consistency.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix well and place in a large oblong baking dish.
Top with 2 cups crushed cornflakes.
Pour 1/2 stick of the melted oleo over cornflakes.
(Crushed Ritz crackers may be used instead of cornflakes but omit the 1/2 stick of melted oleo.)
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza noodle bake
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Layer noodles with mix in a 10 x 10-inch baking dish.
Mix liquids and spices.
Pour over beef and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cookie kisses
directions: Cut dough in 9 slices. Cut each slice in 4 pieces. Lightly spray mini muffin pan with cooking oil spray. Place 1 piece of dough in each cup. Dip mini tart shaper in flour, press into dough to form a cup (flour shaper after each press). Place 1 candy piece in each cup. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool in cups for 15 minutes. Remove to nonstick cooling rack and cool completely.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: brunch scrambled eggs
directions: Melt 1/2 of the butter in large saucepan.
Saute onions and stir in flour.
Gradually add milk and cook until thickened.
Blend in cheese, remove from heat and stir in sherry and spices.
Beat 18 eggs with 1 cup water and season with salt and pepper.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet. Scramble eggs until they barely hold together; set aside to cool. Repeat with remaining eggs.
Grease 2 (3-quart) casseroles.
Pour 1/4 of sauce in each casserole.
Place eggs evenly on top.
If using shrimp, sausage or ham, add at this point.
Cover with remainder of sauce, dividing between the two casseroles.
Entire top and bottom must be covered.
Cover tightly and refrigerate up to 2 days.
Bring to room temperature.
Bake covered at 275° for 1 hour.
Keep warm over hot water.

title: pound cake
directions: Combine all dry ingredients; mix well with wet ingredients. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Mix dry pudding with marshmallows.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Add other ingredients, including juice from pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Break or cut chicken into pieces.
Mix margarine and stuffing mix together.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vanilla, cream and half and half.
Mix well.
Add Eagle Brand and Carnation evaporated milk.
Stir well. Pour into 1 gallon freezer and fill to line with whole milk. Freeze in ice cream freezer for about 40 minutes.
Use lots of ice and add salt often.

title: apricot bars
directions: Stir in
dry ingredients.
Cut in butter.
Pat 2/3 crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with preserves.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 375°
for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut in squares.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and bell pepper.
Add Sloppy Joes mix and taco mix to beef.
Mix well.
Pour into a casserole dish. Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Add tortilla chips around sides and middle.
Place in low oven until cheese melts.

title: strawberry jello sponge cake
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Add strawberries.
Let set while you tear up the cake into small pieces, placing in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour Jell-O mixture over cake.
Refrigerate until firm. Spread Cool Whip on top.
You can use sugar-free Jell-O and lite Cool Whip and have a very low calorie, fat free dessert.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream the eggs and sugar.
Add rest of ingredients, apples last.
Pour into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: unbaked cookies
directions: Mix together; bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa, milk and sugar.
Boil 1 minute.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken and drop on waxed paper.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Lightly brown chicken in garlic butter. Transfer to glass casserole dish. Pour on just enough sauce to "almost cover." Bake at 350° until done (about 30 minutes). Remove from oven and sprinkle on Mozzarella and a generous amount of Parmesan. Return dish to oven and turn oven off. Leave in oven just long enough to melt cheeses.

title: mrs. joe long's key lime pie
directions: Melt shortening. Add flour, sugar, water and beaten egg yolks. Mix well. Cook over hot water until this thickens, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add lime juice and mix well.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover top with meringue and bake in moderate oven until delicate brown.

title: cheese tortilla roll-ups
directions: Spread 1 tablespoon of cream cheese on each tortilla.
Top with 2 slices American cheese and 2 slices ham.
Roll up tightly. Wrap each securely in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.

title: harvard beets
directions: Prepare and cook beets.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, water and lemon juice or vinegar and salt together; cook 5 minutes.
Peel and slice beets; pour mix over beets.
Allow to stand a few minutes before serving.

title: chicken and peas au gratin casserole
directions: Mix bread crumbs with cheese and melted butter.
Line a glass baking dish with half of crumbs.
Top with chicken.
Add the peas. Season with salt and pepper.
Pour mushroom soup over casserole. Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: my favorite
directions: Fold bread.
Put jelly on one side and peanut butter on another side.
Close and eat.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve soda in vinegar; set aside. Cream shortening; add sugar and beat well with electric mixer. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in soda mixture.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Combine buttermilk, vanilla and food coloring.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans. Bake 25 to 35 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and cover with cool water.
Chop tomato, cucumber, onion and bell pepper.
Drain spaghetti and combine with rest of ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: party chicken bites
directions: Skin, bone and separate breasts.
Cut into 2-inch chunks. Separate wings; discard tips.
Put into Dutch oven.
Mix in bowl until blended dressing and preserves.
Add soup mix and mix well. Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until sauce becomes sticky.
Cool and serve.

title: tennessee nuts and bolts
directions: Melt oleo with Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, salt and cayenne pepper.
Mix with all other ingredients and bake at 250° for 2 hours, stirring about 4 times.

title: apple pie
directions: Wash and peel apples.
Cut them into quarters and thinly slice.
Mix sugar, all spices, rind and flour together.
Add to sliced apples.
Coat real good.
Squeeze lemon juice over apples. Let set for a few minutes.
Place into a 9-inch baking pie shell crust.
Pour butter over apples.
Place crust on top; dot with butter.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 15 minutes.
Then lower oven to 350° for about 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chicken with supreme sauce
directions: Put chicken in a buttered flat pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let chicken cool for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Spread mustard over chicken.
Mix cheese, bread crumbs and Italian seasoning.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange-date-nut bread
directions: Pour boiling water over the chopped dates.
Stir until lukewarm.
Beat in by hand margarine, egg, sugar and orange juice concentrate.
Sift together dry ingredients, except nuts.
Fold dry ingredients into date mixture.
Add chopped nuts and blend thoroughly.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan sprayed with Pam and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 55 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Better if eaten immediately or frozen for later use.
Yields 12 servings.

title: golden carrot cookies
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients. Stir in remainder of ingredients. Drop on lightly greased cookie sheet 2-inches apart. Bake until when touched lightly almost no imprint of finger remains. Brown as little as possible. Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Cool. Frost lightly with vanilla frosting.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 3 pan; cake mix, beaten egg and butter. Mix cream cheese, 3 eggs and sugar well. Pour over batter. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Turn down to 325° for 30 minutes.

title: spicy potato soup
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef.
Add potatoes, onion and tomato sauce.
Stir in water, salt, pepper and hot sauce.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening until crumbs are coarse.
Combine egg and milk; add to other mixture all at once. Stir dough until forms a ball.
Turn out and knead gently 20 strokes.
Roll to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter or with glass rim dipped in flour.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet for 10 to 14 minutes at 450°.
It is possible to refrigerate biscuits before baking up to 3 hours.

title: baked hamburger entree
directions: Make patties; cover with mushroom and onion soups.
Bake in oven 2 hours or until done.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy and 1 stick margarine; set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time, added alternately with flour and soda.
With buttermilk, add melted candy and margarine mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake in a greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all together; serve warm with corn chips.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Season pork chops and brown.
Combine soup, milk and water and heat until smooth.
Pour rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer pork chop on top of rice.
Pour liquid over chops and rice.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350° or until liquid is absorbed in rice.
Serves 4.

title: apple-bacon brunch pie
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan in rows. Cover apples with cheese.
Sprinkle with bacon, crumbled.
Beat remaining ingredients together.
Using ladle, pour evenly over apples, cheese and bacon.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Makes a large quantity.
Reserve unbaked mixture in fridge in covered container for up to 6 weeks.
Use as needed.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Mix everything, except butter and cinnamon.
Place in a 13 x 9 1/2-inch baking pan.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with cinnamon. Cover with strips of pie crust.
Start on lower rack of oven at 425° for 30 minutes; finish on second rack at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: quick summer salad
directions: In large glass bowl, rub one crushed garlic clove around bowl and leave in the bottom.
Add all the vegetables and mix them together.
Press in remaining garlic to taste and mix.
Add olive oil, vinegar, oregano and basil and blend into vegetables.
Top with Feta cheese and chill at least 1 hour.
This salad becomes an excellent marinated salad if you leave it in the fridge 3 to 5 days and periodically add additional vinegar.
Enjoy.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix the flour, eggs, water and salt in a bowl.
Place on breadboard and knead in additional flour until the dough is stiff. Roll out thin.
Let dry for 1 hour.

title: left over turkey stew
directions: Put all (except turkey) in a large kettle and cook until almost done.
Then add turkey and finish cooking.
Add a little water if you need to so you have enough liquid.
Serve with homemade bread.

title: lion whiskers
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler or microwave.
Combine pretzels and peanuts in a large bowl.
Pour melted chocolate over pretzels and peanuts; toss quickly.
Spread mixture as thinly as you can and refrigerate for 5 minutes.
Break candy into pieces.

title: apple delicious
directions: Place apple slices in lightly greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish. Melt butter. Blend in flour and sugar. Spread over apples. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: alma's favorite tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, water and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Gradually mix in with wet ingredients.
Chill 40 minutes (important).
Roll and cut out as desired.
Prick tops with fork.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 350° until lightly browned.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Flour can be half whole wheat.
Everything must be at room temperature.
Sift flour, baking powder and sugar, then add raisins and mix in.
Break eggs and mix into buttermilk and add vanilla if desired.
Mix every ingredient together.
Don't overdue the mixing. Finally, add the melted butter.
Set aside for 1/2 hour at room temperature and then turn into greased baking pan.
Rub melted butter across top and cut X on it.
In 20 minutes, put it in preheated 350° oven.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Test by inserting narrow knife.
If no dough adheres, it is done.

title: hamburg goulash
directions: Saute pepper, onion and celery; set aside.
Brown hamburg and add tomatoes.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add sauteed mixture, salt, pepper and sugar.
Simmer slowly for 1/2 hour.
Add cooked macaroni.

title: deep fried seashells
directions: Cook pasta until just tender; drain and rinse with cold water. Stir together egg, crabmeat, shrimp, Cheddar cheese, tomato, chives and pepper.
Fill shells with mixture.
Mix egg with water.
Dip each filled shell into egg mixture, then in crumbs.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Fry, a few at a time, in deep hot 365° oil until golden. Serve with tartar sauce.
Makes 16.

title: green bean-bacon casserole
directions: Cook green beans in boiling, salted water, approximately 25 to 30 minutes; drain.
Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour, salt and sugar, stirring well.
Add milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in mayonnaise, green beans and bacon.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fruit punch
directions: Sprinkle sugar over fruit in a bowl.
Add a small amount of apple juice.
Chill in the refrigerator for several hours. Combine with remaining apple juice, lemon juice, cranberry juice and soda water in punch bowl.
Mix gently.
Yields 20 to 24 servings.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Place layers of potatoes in baking dish, then layer of crumbled meat and onion, until dish if full.
Pour mixture of soup, water and seasoning over potatoes and meat. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour or until done at 350°.

title: white house pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt and eggs together.
Have margarine at room temperature or melt in microwave and add to sugar mixture.
Then add vanilla, syrup and mix.
Add pecans last.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked pork tenderloin
directions: Season tenderloins and roll in flour.
Brown on all sides in butter or oil.
Remove to baking dish.
Lightly brown celery and onion in drippings.
Mix soup mix and water.
Pour in frying pan over onion and celery, then pour over tenderloin.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mash potatoes, salt, pepper and 4 tablespoons butter.
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter and mix with nutmeg and brown sugar.
Spread in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Lay the slices of apple on top.
Spread mashed sweet potato mixture on top of apples.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: kentucky style fried chicken
directions: Mix eggs.
Dip chicken in eggs, then flour, soup and spice mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up, in pan with melted butter. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
The last 5 minutes, sprinkle cheese over chicken. Bake until melted.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower in bite size pieces.
Crumble bacon and slice green onions.
Add mayonnaise, sugar, salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: chocolate chip sensation
directions: Roll out dough onto a rectangular baking pan or stone. Bake according to pkg directions. Set aside to cool. Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix cream cheese and sugar then spread over the cookie. Next mix the pudding and the half and half, let set for a few minutes the pour over the cream cheese mixture. Top with chopped pecans.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine in another bowl egg, milk, vanilla and shortening.
Add dry ingredients and stir only enough to mix well.
Heat deep fat (I use a popcorn popper), then dip up a spoonful of batter and quickly immerse into hot shortening.
Fry a few at a time for 3 to 5 minutes until delicately browned; turn doughnut balls when they come to top. Drain, then place on paper towels.
Cool slightly and drop in paper bag filled with confectioners sugar to coat.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in casserole dish.
Bake at 450° until desired consistency.

title: deep-dish pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 350°.
Stir sugar into eggs until dissolved.
Add syrup, butter, vanilla and nuts.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake on cookie sheet for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove and mash yellow in bowl.
Add all ingredients; mix well.
Refill egg whites; chill.
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix milk, egg, butter, and corn, stir in dry ingredients. Mix well. Drop by spoon fulls into hot oil. Fry until golden brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O as per package.
Cool before mixing in other ingredients and refrigerate.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken in flour and brown in butter.
Remove chicken. Stir soup, seasonings and water into butter.
Stir well and bring to a boil.
Spread dry rice in 1 3/4-quart shallow casserole. Pour all but 1/3 of soup over rice.
Top with chicken and rest of soup.
Bake covered at 375° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: vegetable sandwich filling
directions: Chop vegetables and drain on paper towels; mix gelatin in cold water and let set, then dissolve in boiling water. Mix salt, mayonnaise and gelatin mixture. Stir in vegetables; put in refrigerator at least 5 hours or overnight. Serve on whole wheat, whole grain or your choice of bread.

title: chili beans
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and chili powder.
After beef is browned, add tomato soup and water and kidney beans; stir.
Then add sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and let simmer on low for 15 minutes.

title: jello peach pie
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch, jello and water to a boil.
Liquid will turn clear and should stick to a spoon.
Add peaches.
Pour into a prebaked 9 inch pie shell (may use deep dish).
Refrigerate until jelled.
Serve with Cool Whip on top.
Other fruit (such as strawberries) may be used as well, with matching jello.

title: pinwheel cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla, beating until light.
Gradually add flour mixture, beating until blended.
Divide dough in half.
Add cocoa to half of dough.
Roll each piece of dough on lightly floured wax paper to form a 9 x 12-inch rectangle 1/8-inch thick. Place chocolate layer on top of butterscotch layer.
Remove waxed paper; roll dough lengthwise to form a 12-inch roll.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill until firm.
Slice 1/8-inch thick.
Bake on lightly greased sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: double apple cake
directions: Cream butter
and
brown
sugar
until smooth.	Beat in eggs, one at
a time.
Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt. Stir into butter mixture.
Stir in apples, applesauce, raisins and nuts. Dough
should
be
stiff.
Spoon into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and
spread
evenly.
Bake	at
for 35 to 45 minutes or until
cake
shrinks
from sides of pan and springs back when lightly touched.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: applesauce meat balls
directions: Beat egg with milk, add stuffing; let stand 5 minutes or until stuffing mix is soft.
Beat until smooth and fluffy.
Add meat, applesauce, onion, salt and pepper.
Make into small balls.

title: mom's blender pecan pie
directions: Put eggs, sugar, salt, corn syrup, butter & vanilla in blender and blend well.
Add 1 c pecans and blend just enough to chop nuts coarsely.
Pour into pie shell, place pecan halves on top.
Bake in hot oven (425 degrees) 15 minutes; reduce heat to 350 degrees and continue baking until top is lightly browned, about 30 minutes.

title: "orange" pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in baking pan. Mix all other ingredients and pour over pork chops. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally. Serves 4.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix all chopped vegetables, bacon and crumbled cornbread together.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice and pour over ingredients.
