title: wonderful waffles(breakfast)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and salt in a medium bowl. Stir in milk, margarine and egg yolk until blended.
Beat egg white in a small bowl on high speed until stiff peaks form.
Fold flour mixture in egg white.
Pour 2/3 cup of batter into center of hot waffle iron.
Bake until steaming stops.
Makes three 8-inch waffles.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients; mix.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie dish.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 50 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Add enough water to make 1 cup liquid. Bring to boil and put on jello.
Stir.
Cool.
Add pineapple, nuts, celery and cranberry sauce.
Mix well and chill.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Beat egg
whites stiff; add slightly beaten yolks.
Add sugar, sifted flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and hot milk with butter in
it.
Bake
at
for
to 35 minutes in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bacon cheddar puffs
directions: Bring milk and margarine to a boil over medium heat.
Add flour all at once, stirring constantly, until mixture forms a ball and leaves side of pan.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons on greased foil-lined cookie sheet.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Freeze well. Reheat in a 350° oven for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Rinse and drain beans.
In a large pot with a lid, place beans and cover with water.
Add ham bone and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 40 minutes.
Add sausage, cover and cook for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add garlic, onions, celery, green pepper and bay leaf.
Continue cooking, covered, 1 1/2 hours, or until soft.
Add Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce, parsley and salt.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove bay leaf; serve over rice.

title: cottage cheese dill bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast in warm water.
Stir until blended. Stir in 2 teaspoons sugar and set aside. Combine cottage cheese, onion, dill weed, baking powder, salt, 2 tablespoons sugar and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Add yeast mixture.
Mix well.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl. Turn to bring greased side on top. Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down.
Make in 2 loaves. Brush top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients; cut in oleo.
Add eggs and milk mixture.
Fold in berries.
Bake at 350°, about 20 minutes.

title: grandma's sugar cream pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour well.
Add vanilla to the cream, then the cream mixture to the flour mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell and place pie pan on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Combine and mix.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oven pot roast
directions: Place meat on heavy-duty foil.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over meat.
Spread mushroom soup over this.
Fold foil snugly around meat; place in shallow baking dish.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: applesauce cake(diabetic or sugar-free)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and add to eggs, applesauce, oil and sweetener that have been beaten until smooth.
Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until brown. Bake in either loaf or tube pan.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: In electric skillet at 350°, cut bacon in small pieces and brown.
Cut up cabbage; add to the bacon and bacon grease.
Cook until done.
Cook noodles and drain.
Add cooked noodles to cabbage and mix.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Wash squash and cut in half lengthwise.
Remove and discard seeds.
Using a spoon, remove and save small chunks of squash until only the thick shell remains.
Brown ground chuck lightly and drain.
Add rice, onion, squash chunks and spaghetti sauce. Place squash in a pan, cut sides up.
Fill firmly with meat and rice mixture.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Place pecans in bottom of a greased sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle coconut over pecans.
Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix butter, sugar and cream cheese together.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake according to package directions.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix and chill for 24 hours.

title: condensed milk
directions: Mix milk and water in mixer.
Add sugar.
Blend until dissolved.
Let stand in refrigerator until thick.
(Will help you out of a pinch.)

title: layered dip
directions: Layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan in this order: beans, avocado dip, sour cream, picante sauce, cheese, tomatoes and black olives.
Get a bag of tortilla chips and enjoy.

title: vegetarian egg bake(serves 4)
directions: Cook zucchini and onion in corn oil in large skillet until lightly browned, about 10 minutes, stirring often.
Add eggplant, green peppers and garlic; cover and cook 5 minutes.
Stir in parsley, salt, oregano, basil and white pepper.
Top with tomato wedges.
Cover and cook until tomatoes soften, about 3 minutes.

title: neffles
directions: Mix eggs and flour until thick and sticky.
Put cooked potato cubes into a pan with water.
In a frying pan, burn the butter, then pour the burnt butter over the potatoes and water.
Drop the egg mix into the potatoes and water with a teaspoon.
Heat the soup until hot.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: ham and cheese pretzel pick-ups
directions: In small bowl, combine cheese, ham, horseradish, mustard and hot pepper sauce.
Mix well.
Shape cheese mixture into 48 (3/4-inch) balls.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or until serving.

title: pumpkin chiffon
directions: Take graham cracker crumbs, butter and 1/4 cup sugar and mix well.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Set aside.
Take cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar and eggs and mix together.
Pour onto crust.
Bake 22 minutes at 350°.
Let cool, then mix pumpkin, pudding, milk, cinnamon and Cool Whip and spread on cooled crust.
Top with more Cool Whip, if desired.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in water.
Add pineapple juice. Add 7-Up last.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine soups and broth; boil.
Remove from heat and add chives, mushrooms and cheese, stirring until cheese melts.
Spoon 1/2 rice into dish, top with 1/2 chicken and pour 1/2 sauce over it.
Repeat steps.
Top with pimentos.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with foil while baking.

title: 5 hour beef stew
directions: Place meat
and
vegetables
in
baking dish.
Sprinkle tapioca, salt and sugar, then pour on tomato juice.
Cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: chess squares
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs.
Mix well and pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, lemon juice, 2 eggs and powdered sugar until smooth.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and refrigerate.
Cut into squares before serving.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening; add sugar gradually and continue creaming until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add egg and mix well.
Sift flour with salt and baking powder.
Mix cocoa with dry ingredients. Add alternately with the milk to the creamed mixture, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend in vanilla.
Drop dough onto slightly rounded teaspoon, one at a time onto lightly greased baking sheet about an inch apart.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° until lightly browned, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove to cooling rack immediately.
Makes about 70 cookies.

title: oven steak
directions: Cut steak into small pieces; salt and pepper to taste.
Coat in flour and brown quickly in skillet with oil.
Place steak in large covered baking dish.
Mix canned soup and water.
Pour over steak.
Cover and place in oven.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: old fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift first four ingredients together into a large bowl.
Add oatmeal, sugars, shortening, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Add remaining ingredients. Beat until blended.
Drop by teaspoonful on prepared greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° in moderately hot oven about 12 minutes or until browned.
(I bake at 350°.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add the rest.
Melt butter in an iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange jello
directions: Mix orange jello with 1 cup boiling water. After mixing, add 1 pint orange sherbet and other ingredients.
Pour into a large dish and refrigerate.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients except cabbage, adding mayonnaise to desired thickness and taste.
Shred or grate cabbage and mix well.

title: aunt ann's brownies
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Melt together butter, sugar and water, then stir in 1/2 package chocolate chips.
Cool. Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture, remaining chocolate chips and nuts. Bake in 9-inch square buttered pan. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 325°. Cool and cut into bars.

title: chicken rice-a-celli
directions: Melt margarine in frypan.
Add vermicelli pieces and raw rice. Stir over low heat until vermicelli pieces are brown.
Dissolve chicken soup base in 1/2 cup boiling water.
Add enough boiling water to soup mixture to make 3 cups liquid.
Slowly add to rice and vermicelli.
Sprinkle and stir in parsley and sage or poultry seasoning.
Increase heat to medium-high.
Cover and cook until no liquid remains, about 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Combine first two ingredients; cool.
Mix rest of ingredients. Bake in a greased cake pan for 35 to 40 minutes.
Good without icing.

title: ranch pretzels
directions: Mix ranch dressing mix, salt, cayenne pepper and oil in large zip lock bag.
Add pretzels and mix well.
Bake at 200 degrees for 2 hours, turning pretzels every 30 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water; add baking mix and milk.
Knead 10 times using a small amount of flour to prevent sticking.
Roll to 1/2 inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet and let rise in warm oven about 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 425° and bake biscuits 6 to 8 minutes.

title: pineapple pudding cake
directions: Bake for 30 minutes or until done at 350°. Have icing ready to pour on hot cake.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix margarine and sugar; cream well. Add eggs, one at a time, then buttermilk.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish pie shell. Bake at 275° to 300° for 45 minutes.

title: spiced rum pumpkin chiffon
directions: Soften gelatin in apple juice in a saucepan; let stand 1 minute.
Stir over medium heat for 1 minute, until gelatin is dissolved.
Set aside.
Dissolve the cornstarch in milk in a saucepan.
Stir over medium-high heat until lightly thickened, about 2 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar and molasses and remove pan from heat.
Beat egg yolks until frothy.
Whisk into milk-cornstarch over medium-high heat until the mixture is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat in cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, pumpkin and dissolved gelatin.
Turn into bowl and chill until mixture mounds slightly, 1 to 3 hours.
Beat egg whites with salt until soft peaks form.
Beat in sugar and continue to beat until stiff peaks form.
Beat in milk powder and rum.
Fold in pumpkin mixture.
Divide among 6 to 8 parfait glasses and chill 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken delight
directions: Put chicken in shallow baking pan.
In separate bowl, combine mushroom soup, onion soup mix and pepper.
Spoon over chicken. Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken biscuits
directions: In the melted margarine, saute onion, celery, Tabasco sauce and Worcestershire sauce until vegetables are soft.
Add chicken and mix together.
Salt to taste.
With a rolling pin, roll up and pinch ends together to seal.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and add dressing, Salad Supreme, tomato, cucumber and onions.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot punch
directions: Mix - put into large pot and heat.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Cook raisins 20 minutes; set aside.
Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
Melt shortening.
Measure flour after sifting.

title: tiny cheese puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Grease baking sheet. Combine cheese, salt, hot water and margarine in kettle and bring to boil. Remove from heat. Add flour and then beaten egg. Drop by teaspoonfuls on prepared baking sheet. Bake 15 minutes. Best served warm.

title: easy spinach lasagna
directions: Mix tomatoes, sauce and water and place a small amount in bottom of 9 x 12-inch deep foil baking pan.
Layer 3 dry noodles. Mix Ricotta and spinach and layer with noodles and sauce.
Add some Cheddar along with garlic and basil.
Pour remaining sauce on top and Mozzarella last with parsley and any remaining Cheddar. Cover with foil.
This can all be done ahead of time.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil last 30 minutes.
Let sit 30 minutes before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Pare sweet potatoes; cook until almost done.
Combine sweet potatoes, 1/2 cup sugar, 1 egg, 1/2 stick butter and cinnamon; mix well.
Spread mix in baking pan.

title: celia's mexican salsa
directions: Peel the tomatillos and boil in 1 cup of water until softened. While the tomatillos are boiling, toast the Chile de Arbols in a pan on top of the stove for about 5 minutes on medium heat or until they look toasted.
When the tomatillos are soft and the Chile de Arbols are toasted, place the following in a blender:
the water the tomatillos were boiled in, 1/2 of the tomatillos, 2 pieces of fresh garlic and the toasted Chile de Arbols.
Blend until smooth, then add the other half of the tomatillos and press the grater button on the blender for only a couple of seconds.
Add salt to taste.

title: tuna pasta salad
directions: Combine all ingredients (except peas and macaroni) thoroughly. Add macaroni and peas.
Chill for 2 hours.
Each serving containers 1.1 grams of fat.

title: meat balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place meatballs in baking dish.
Mix Worcestershire sauce, dry mustard and catsup.
Pour over meatballs and bring to a boil. Let simmer for 1 hour.

title: lemon custard
directions: Mix in a small bowl the egg yolk, sugar, lemon rind, lemon juice and salt.
In a quart bowl, put egg white, water and nonfat dry milk; beat with a rotary beater at high speed, until the mixture stands in peaks.
Gradually beat in the lemon mixture. Turn into a 1-quart ice tray.
Sprinkle the graham cracker crumbs over the top; freeze without stirring, at the coldest temperature, until firm.
Serves 4.

title: frozen strawberry jam
directions: Wash and dry 6 half-pint fruit jars.
(You can use plastic cartons, plastic bowls, etc.).
Mix berries and sugar and set aside for 10 minutes.
Mix Certo and lemon juice.
Add to berries and sugar (after the 10 minutes).
Stir constantly for 3 minutes. Fill jars to 1/2-inch from the top.
Wipe top of jar and put lid on.
Let set at room temperature for 24 hours.
Freeze.
When taken out of freezer, refrigerate.
Will keep in refrigerator for 3 weeks.

title: chopped steak for a large party
directions: Mix all together and make into 10 ounce patties.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Drain potatoes.
In a large bowl, while hot, mash potatoes slightly and mix in all ingredients except 3 of the sliced eggs. Decorate top of potato salad with eggs.
Sprinkle with paprika lightly.
Let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Overnight is best.

title: jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Separate pineapple and juice.
Dissolve gelatine in pineapple juice.
Add strawberries to Jell-O mixture, then pour in crushed pineapple.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Boil the first four ingredients for about 10 minutes.
Cool, add spices, salt and soda.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla in huge bowl.
Mix well and add remaining ingredients.
Flour hands; make balls.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cookies in blender to look like potting soil (a few at a time).
Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar; set aside. Mix Cool Whip, milk and pudding.
Then mix cream cheese mixture and pudding mixture together.
In flowerpot, layer cookies (thin layer) and filling mixture.
Be sure to end up with cookies on top. Refrigerate 6 hours; garnish with plants or flowers and serve with gardening shovel.

title: red snapper a la grecque(baked red snapper with feta cheese)
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Wipe the fish fillets with a damp cloth.
Heat 2 tablespoons of the oil in a saucepan and add the onion and garlic.
Cook, stirring, until onion is wilted.
Add the tomatoes with tomato paste, capers, oregano, pepper flakes, 1/4 cup chopped parsley and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 10 minutes.
Put the remaining 2 tablespoons of oil in a baking dish, preferably oval, large enough to hold the fish in one layer. Arrange the fish skin side up in the dish.
Pour the tomato sauce over all.
Place the dish on top of the stove and bring the sauce to the boil.
Put the dish in the oven and bake 15 minutes. Sprinkle with Feta cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.
Sprinkle with ouzo and remaining 2 tablespoons chopped parsley.
Serve piping hot.
Yield:
Four servings.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter an 11 x 14-inch pan.
Put half the bread cubes in bottom.
Add half the cheese, then sausage mixed with crumbled bacon.
Add remaining bread and cheese.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over other ingredients. Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until brown and done.
Serves 12.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, peanut butter, salt and egg. Add all the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press a crisscross on each ball with tines of fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: favorite maple syrup
directions: Combine sugar, water and corn syrup in saucepan.
Heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture boils.
Cover and boil gently 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
When syrup is cool, add maple flavoring.
Blend well.

title: marc's favorite lunch
directions: Start at 10 a.m.
Eat banana and drink a cup of milk.
Eat apple and drink another cup of milk.
Eat 2 of the pickles. About noon time, share the ravioli with mom. Drink another cup of milk.
Pour all the olives in a big bowl and put onto the end of each 10 fingers.
Eat one at a time with cartoons.
Drink a cup of fruit drink.
Before 3 p.m., eat some more pickles and drink another cup of milk. This is a fun all day lunch.

title: drop rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, egg and oil.
Mix in flour and blend well.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
Grease muffin tins and fill
1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes. (Mixture will last 2 weeks in refrigerator.)

title: tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, celery, onions, apple and mayonnaise. Mix well and store in refrigerator.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt
margarine
in baking dish. Sweeten peaches with 1 cup sugar.
Mix 1 cup sugar with flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour
over margarine.
Add fruit last (do not stir).
Bake 1 hour or until brown.

title: orange chicken and burgundy
directions: Brown
chicken	in
margarine.	Season	with
salt
and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients, except Burgundy and orange slices.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 35 minutes.
Add Burgundy and cook 10 minutes more.

title: swiss and frank spirals
directions: Cut a lengthwise slit in each wiener; insert strip of cheese in each.
Quarter 8 biscuits.
(Bake remaining with appetizers.) Shape quarters in 4-inch strips.
Wind, spiral fashion, around each wiener.
Place on baking sheet; brush with butter and sprinkle with sesame.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes or until browned.
Serve warm.
Makes 32.

title: mary's chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook the 1 cup chopped onion and garlic in the 2 tablespoons oil until onion is tender but not brown; stir in flour.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce, chili peppers, sugar, cumin and the 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; set aside.
Combine chicken, half the cheese, the 1/4 cup onion, the chopped olive and the 3/4 teaspoon salt.
Set aside.

title: herb chicken casserole
directions: Bone chicken and add to all the ingredients.
Cover with bag of stuffing (prepared).
Pour melted margarine over all. Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
(I add celery and onion to taste to stuffing mix.)

title: mexican soup
directions: Cook hamburger. Drain. Open all canned vegetables together, onion. Add taco seasoning and Ranch dressing. Add all together 2 cups water. Cook until onion is tender.

title: artichoke hors d' oeuvres
directions: Stir together in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° approximately 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Salt the cucumbers well, let stand 1 hour and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients, bring to boil.
Add cucumbers and bring to a boil.
Pack in jars.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, saute onion and garlic in olive oil.
Add ground beef; brown.
Drain off fat.
Add tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Chop whole tomatoes and add to pot. Sprinkle with sugar, Italian seasoning (oregano, basil, rosemary, sage, marjoram and thyme), pepper and add bay leaf.
Also, add hot pepper.
Simmer for at least one hour uncovered.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple, saving liquid.
Add enough water to make one cup liquid and add to gelatin mixture.
Stir in drained blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart flat pan.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Clean or thaw shrimp.
Saute onion, celery, and garlic in oil until tender.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, worcestershire, salt, sugar, chili powder, tabasco, and okra.
Simmer uncovered for 45 minutes.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes. Add file and stir just before serving over rice.

title: creamy pralines
directions: Advance Preparation: Put down generous amounts of waxed paper over thickness of newspaper on counter. Have a cup of water with 1 large ice cube to test soft-ball stage available.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add can of condensed milk. Beat with mixer.
Beat the eggs.
Add the lemon juice and egg mixture to condensed milk and cream cheese mixture.
Beat until smooth. Pour into 2 pie crusts. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until firm.
Top with 2 cans strawberry filling.
You may prefer to use fresh strawberries.

title: three hour rolls
directions: Combine sugar and shortening in large bowl.
Add the scalded milk.
When the mixture is cool, add the yeast and salt.
Stir thick with flour.
Let rise 2 hours, roll and shape into rolls. Raise 1 hour and bake at 350° to 375°.
Makes about 18 rolls.

title: fluffy fruit dip
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Chill for at least 1 hour.
Chop fruits and serve with the dip.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix the flour, margarine and pecans; put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour half of mixture into a baking dish.
Put in raw hamburger, Ortega peppers and cheese. Cover with rest of cornbread mixture and cheese.
Bake 1 hour.

title: light rolls
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and yeast dissolved in a cup of lukewarm water and 2 teaspoon sugar.
Add 2 cups more of lukewarm water and 8 cups flour.
Refrigerate over night.
Make out and bake at 350 degrees temperature.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients; add egg.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Blend rest of ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out; cut desired shapes.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, soda, salt and 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Mix in apples and nuts.
Bake 1 hour in a Bundt or tube pan at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix up real good and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: quick upside-down cake
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and place in baking pan.
Pour cake batter on top and bake cake as directed on package.
When cake is done, invert onto cake platter.

title: perfect chocolate cake
directions: In medium bowl, combine cocoa and boiling water; beat until smooth.
Cool.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
In large bowl, beat butter, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
At low speed add flour mixture in four parts, alternating with cocoa mix.
Put filling between layers, then frost.

title: puff the magic pie(from richard simmons' deal-a-meal cookbook)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Steam or microwave vegetables until just tender; drain.
Toss in bowl with herbs and pepper; set aside.
Put butter in a 10-inch pie plate and set in oven until melted.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk and beat until well blended.
Add flour and salt and beat until batter is smooth. Pour batter into heated pie plate.
Spread vegetables evenly over batter to within 1 inch of edge.
Bake 30 minutes or until brown and puffy.
Cut in wedges.
Serve.
Yields 6 servings (268 calories each).

title: aunt joyce's 500~ roast and potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Punch holes in the roast with a fork. Baste it well with your choice of sauce and rub it down with Morton's Nature's Seasons.
Place the roast in an open roaster or pan.
Do not cover.
Wrap the potatoes separately in tinfoil. Place the roast and the potatoes into the preheated 500° oven. Bake at a rate of 5 minutes per pound.
Turn the oven off!
Leave the roast and potatoes in the oven for 2 more hours.
Serve and enjoy!

title: paradise chicken
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Brown chicken in butter. Drain.
Combine syrup, soy sauce and garlic and pour over chicken.
Cover; simmer 30 minutes, turning chicken once.
Remove chicken.
Add pineapple, bell pepper, celery, green onion and papaya to pan.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/2 cup of water.
Stir into pan.
Bring to a boil.
When thickened, spoon over chicken. Serve.

title: miracle salmon loaf
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients; add salmon and bread crumbs to mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 5-inch greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no sugar cookies
directions: Puree bananas.
Mix dates, nuts and raisins together.
Pour bananas over this mixture.
Add just enough oatmeal or granola to effect cookie dough.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and bake on a greased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Watch carefully as they burn easily.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken stuff
directions: Chop chicken into bite sized pieces.
Heat oil.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Batter chicken with it.
Simmer in fry pan with the oil.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to browned chicken. Simmer in covered pan for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix in large pitcher. Follow instructions on can of lemonade as directed. Add berries and 7-Up. Chill; serve over ice.

title: low calorie dessert
directions: Mix well the cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Pour on top of graham cracker crumbs.
Top with cherries.
Chill overnight. Enjoy!

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and drain; add the spaghetti sauce to the meat.
Mix in small bowl the eggs; beat well with cottage cheese, 1/3 Mozzarella cheese and pepper and salt to taste.
Boil about 15 minutes.
Spread 2 big spoons of sauce in bottom of pan, then layer noodles, cheese filling, then sauce.
Do this until pan is full.
Top with rest of cheese in bag.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cover with foil and bake.
Let stand for 30 minutes before serving.

title: pour pizza crust
directions: Beat until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch or 13 x 17-inch greased pan.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Fry bacon and onion; set aside.
Cook potatoes and carrots until tender; add zucchini last 8 to 10 minutes.
Put potatoes, carrots and zucchini in blender; add salt and pepper to taste. Add chicken broth and butter; blend.
Heat, adding chopped bacon and onion.
Serve.

title: meat crust pie
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onions, green pepper, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, seasonings, and 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce.
Mix well and pat into bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie plate. Combine remaining 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce, 1/2 teaspoon salt, water, rice and 1/2 cup of the cheese.
Spoon mixture into meat shell.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Top with tomato slices and remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, 10 to 15 minutes longer.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: homemade bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; mix well.
mix dry ingredients together and cut in shortening add to yeast mixture with oil. Cover with cloth and let rise twice.
Divide in to 4 greased loaf pans.
Let rise again.
Bake at 375 for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients well and put in casserole dish. Spread next 3 ingredients over mixture and sprinkle with pecans just before baking.
The first ingredients can be made the day before and refrigerated.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, covered. Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: yummy chocolate candy
directions: Microwave first 3 ingredients on High for 1 minute and blend together in large bowl.
Alternate additional time in microwave and blending until mixture has a glossy appearance.
Stir in oatmeal and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper to cool.

title: warm chicken-bean salad
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch strips.
Set strips aside.
Combine 2 tablespoons oil, lemon juice, salt, cumin and pepper in a small bowl; stir well.
Reserve 1 tablespoon oil mixture; set remaining oil mixture aside.
Place reserved oil mixture in a medium bowl. Add chicken strips, and toss to coat.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator 10 to 15 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Cook beans until tender.
Add seasoning and cook 30 minutes more, then add chicken and green chilies.
Cook another 15 minutes until done.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Mix Bisquick, milk and soup together. Add sausage; mix together.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Fill tins 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 11 minutes.

title: evan's favorite sandwiches
directions: Mix in food processor.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Pound chicken pieces down a little with the edge of a saucer or the bottom of a wine bottle.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper and coat with flour.
In a skillet, brown chicken in oleo over medium heat for about 5 minutes or until lightly brown.
Add a little more oleo to pan; add mushrooms, garlic powder, chicken broth, lemon juice and parsley flakes.
Simmer 7 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until sauce slightly thickens.
Add more broth and/or lemon juice as desired.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Put in crock-pot; add Velveeta cheese, 1/4 cup milk and tomatoes.
Cook on low until melted. Serve with Tostitos.

title: how to clean a chicken
directions: You will need newspapers.

title: "pastor" pasta(a.k.a. tuna noodle casserole)
directions: Boil macaroni and place in large bowl.
Dice tuna, green pepper and onion.
Add these and relish to macaroni.
Add mayo and mix well.
Add salt and pepper, then mix well.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add almond extract and Cool Whip. Chill.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix the melted shortening with the sugar and molasses; blend thoroughly.
Add the beaten egg and the soda which has been dissolved in the hot water.
Mix in the vanilla.
Have ready the flour which has been mixed and sifted with the cream of tartar, spices and salt; add and mix thoroughly.
Let stand in a cool place for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Roll to about 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut and place on greased cookie tins.
Bake in 400° oven until done. Watch the baking because molasses products burn easily at this temperature, but a softer cookie results.

title: french-dip roast beef
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash beef roast and place in pan with 1 1/2 cups of water.
Cover and seal with aluminum foil; bake until done.
Remove roast.
Add au jus mix to roast drippings, along with 3 cups of water.
Stir and cook over medium heat.
Slice or chunk roast and serve on toasted steak rolls.
Serve au jus gravy on side for dipping sandwich.
Serve with potato chips and cranberry sauce.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix in glass container.
Dissolve citric acid in 1/4 cup hot water.
Dissolve sugar in 2 quarts hot water.
Mix into sugar solution the Wyler's drink mix; cool.
Add pineapple juice and cold water.
Add food color gradually until desired color is achieved while stirring.
May be frozen.
If frozen, allow to thaw approximately 3 hours until slushy.
Serves 50.

title: butter fingers
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour to which the nuts and salt have been added.
Pinch off tiny pieces.
Roll between the palms to make a roll like the finger.
Bake about 30 minutes in oven at 375°.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: chicken delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Carefully layer all ingredients (in the order listed) in a baking dish.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend cream cheese, sour cream, diced onion, seasoned salt and pepper.
Spread 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick on platter.
Next, layer with lettuce, cheese, tomatoes and olives. Drizzle taco or picante sauce over top just before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: egg and pickle potato salad
directions: Bring water, dried onion and 1/2 teaspoon salt to boiling. Add potatoes.
Cook, covered, for 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Drain well; cool slightly.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus on bottom.
Mix soup and asparagus juice and pour over asparagus.
Mix grated cheese and crushed crackers together and pour on top.
Pour melted butter over all and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: dinosaur treats
directions: Microwave:
Melt margarine 45 seconds.
Add marshmallows; mix well.
Heat 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring after 45 seconds.
Add cereal; mix well.
Press firmly into 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan; cool.
Turn onto cutting surface, peel off foil.

title: orange coconut cream pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk in 1 1/2-quart microwave-safe bowl; blend well.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Stir well and cook for 2 minutes longer, then stir again and cook 1 minute or until mixture comes to a boil.
Stir in orange juice and rind.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Chill.

title: strawberry loaf
directions: Fold into flour mixture, stirring just enough to moisten. Spoon into 2 well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until they test done.

title: egg rolls
directions: Chop up carrots, long green onions and onions.
Mix in large salad bowl with the hamburger meat.
Add salt, pepper, garlic powder, sesame oil and eggs.
Mix really well with hands.
Lay out egg roll wraps and fill them up.
Deep fry until brown.

title: chicken soup
directions: Put chicken, water, salt, onion, peppercorns, 3 stalks celery, all celery leaves and 3 carrots in a soup kettle.
Cover and bring to boil.
Skim off foam.
Reduce heat to simmer and cook for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Remove meat, veggies and peppercorns.
Strain stock if desired.
Chill stock then skim fat layer.
Dice remaining celery and carrots; add to stock.
Cook until tender.
Remove meat from bones and dice.
Add chicken, rice or noodles and parsley.
Stir in coloring and bouillon.

title: five-can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in casserole and top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs, then dry ingredients.
Roll in waxed paper and refrigerate until hard.
Cut into thin slices and bake in moderate (350°) oven.

title: cracklin corn bread
directions: Sift corn meal and flour together.
Mix egg and milk and add to dry ingredients.
Mix well and add cracklins.
Bake in greased pan in 425° oven for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix peeled and sliced peaches and sugar.
Set aside.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Put butter in a deep dish and melt in oven.

title: old fashioned peanut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2 or 3 large cookie sheets.
Grind 3/4 cup peanuts in food processor, just until fine.
Chop remaining 1/2 cup peanuts; set aside.
Beat butter, sugar, maple syrup and maple extract in large bowl with mixer at medium speed until fluffy.
Beat eggs in well.
Stir dry ingredients in small bowl to mix well.
Gradually beat into creamed mixture at low speed until smooth.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped peanuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto prepared cookie sheet, 1-inch apart. Bake 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.
Cool.
Brush top of each cookie with corn syrup.
Sprinkle with finely ground peanuts. Dust with 10x sugar.

title: green salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in boiling water; then add cheese and mayonnaise until dissolved.
Add milk and pineapple.
Place in salad mold until firm.

title: fruit and nut muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine apples, sugar, raisins and nuts.
Set aside.
In another bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla.
Stir into apple mixture.
Combine dry ingredients and carefully fold into apple mixture.
Do not overmix.

title: grandma's fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Drain mandarin oranges; do not reserve juice.
Beat dry pudding into pineapple juice until thickened.
Fold oranges and pineapple into pudding mixture. Refrigerate.
Slice bananas into mixture just before serving.

title: easy apple dessert
directions: Cut the apples in half and core.
Slice thinly.
You do not need to peel the apples, if you wish.
Drop slices into a bowl of cold water.
Set aside.

title: brownie oatmeal gems
directions: In a
2-quart
saucepan, stir chocolate and butter over low heat
just until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat.
Stir in corn syrup, eggs and salt.

title: taco salad
directions: Fry meat well and drain.
Place meat back in pan.
Add taco seasoning in meat and water as directed on package.
Let simmer on low heat until you have everything else ready.
Put lettuce, tomatoes and bell pepper in large bowl or pan.
Crush unsalted chips, not too small, and place over vegetables.
Pour meat mixture over all and mix well.
Serve with picante sauce to your taste.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; jell until starting to thicken. Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl.
Add all ingredients to jello.
Pour in mold.
(A ring mold can be used.)

title: green rice(casserole)
directions: Cook rice and broccoli in separate pots.
Drain.
While these are cooking, saute onions and celery in a dab of oleo in a skillet.
Add soup to broccoli and cheese to the rice.
Add sauteed stuff and bake in a Pyrex dish at 350° for 20 minutes. Put crushed Ritz crackers and paprika on top.

title: chili(serves 8)
directions: Cook garlic in oil until golden.
Crumble meat in pieces and cook for 10 minutes.

Pour off some of the oil and drippings into another skillet and cook sliced onions and green peppers until tender. Add to meat with tomatoes, kidney beans, tomato paste, chili powder, vinegar, cayenne powder, cloves, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook over low heat for 1 hour.
If too dry, add additional tomatoes.
If too much liquid, uncover and simmer longer.

title: tennessee bread pudding
directions: Combine water and sugar in a bowl, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Add milk and eggs, stirring with a wire whisk until blended.
Stir in coconut and next 5 ingredients.
Add bread cubes; let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm with Bourbon Sauce.
Makes 12 servings.

title: hot chili cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips.
Heat, stirring occasionally, over low heat until cheese melts.
Serve as a dip or pour over chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: microwave toffee
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup pecans in a 9-inch circle on a greased sheet; set aside.
Coat top 2 inches of a 2 1/2 quart glass bowl with butter. Put rest in bowl.
Add sugar, salt and water.
Do not stir!
Microwave at High 11 minutes or until light brown.
Pour over pecans.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips.
Sprinkle with the 1/4 cup other nuts.
Chill until firm.
Break into bite size pieces. Yields 1 pound.

title: creamy southwest soup(spicy, lots of flavor)
directions: Brown bacon and onion in large saucepan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Add all remaining ingredients except sour cream and simmer over medium heat about 20 minutes.
Stir in sour cream just before serving.
Recipe makes 6 servings.
Ultra low-fat.

title: fried okra
directions: Wash and dry okra with paper towel.
Cut in 1-inch pieces or use very small whole okra.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place okra in plastic bag in which corn meal has been seasoned with your favorite herbs (Season-All, garlic powder).
Fry in deep skillet with shortening until golden crisp.
Drain.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Combine milk and eggs and stir in oil.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Stir only enough to mix. Grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: zucchini stuffing
directions: Steam zucchini until tender.
Drain.
Melt margarine.
Brown onion and pepper.
Mix with stuffing.
Mix all ingredients. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: carrot spice cake
directions: In saucepan, combine apple juice, honey, water, carrots, raisins, margarine and spices.
Bring to boil over medium heat. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool 1 hour, stirring occasionally to release steam.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream
sugar and Crisco.
Add flour, baking powder and eggs. Add soda to sour milk. Stir and add to flour mixture.
Add mashed bananas and vanilla.
Bake in two layer cake pans, greased and floured, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: e-z burgundy stew
directions: Quarter or chop any of the following:
onion, bell pepper and mushrooms.
Cook in a covered Dutch oven at 300° for 4 hours. Great served with noodles.

title: snickerdoodles(makes 6 dozen)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and eggs thoroughly. Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Keep the popped corn warm in a 200° oven.
Melt the caramels in the top of a double boiler over simmering water.
Add the corn syrup and water and mix until smooth.
Slowly pour over the popcorn in a large bowl or pan.
Stir to mix well.
With greased hands, shape the mixture into balls about the size of soft balls.
Let the balls cool and dry completely before wrapping.
(You can make them the day before.)
Wrap in plastic wrap or in plastic bags.
Yield: 15 popcorn balls.

title: yummy baked beans
directions: Fry hamburger.
Season with salt, pepper, garlic powder, seasoned salt and celery salt.
Drain.
Add green pepper and onion.
Cook until slightly tender.
Put all ingredients in baking dish.
Heat in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: banana split
directions: Blend cracker crumbs and 1 stick of butter in bottom of dish to form crust.
Mix cream cheese, 1 stick of butter and sugar.
Beat until fluffy.
Make a layer over the crust.
Make a layer of bananas (sliced).
Add pineapple and top with Cool Whip, nuts and cherries.

title: matzo stuffing
directions: Place matzo crumbs in large bowl.
Finely chop onions and celery and add to crumbs.
Measure out spices and add to mixture. Heat chicken stock until hot but not boiling.
Whip egg slightly with fork.
Add butter, egg and hot stock to the matzo crumb mixture.
Toss mixture until moistened.
Yields enough to stuff a roasting chicken or small turkey.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix together and roll into balls.
Roll balls in powdered sugar.
Bake until brown at 400°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and put in buttered casserole dish.
Toss cracker crumbs with melted oleo and put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all well.
Bake for 2 hours at 300° to 325°.
Could be topped with buttered crushed cornflakes before baking.

title: turkey breast scallopini with marsala
directions: Place turkey between wax paper and pound until 1/4-inch thick. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; dredge through flour and pat lightly.

title: three-bean baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef, bacon and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: corn and cheddar cheese chowder
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil in salted water with bay leaves and cumin until tender, 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Saute onion and add flour.
Mix well and add milk. Pour into potatoes and water.
Add corn, parsley, chives, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir in grated Cheddar cheese and white wine.
Mix well. Heat until cheese is completely melted.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix all vegetables well.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup salt and let stand for 1 hour.
In the meantime, put 4 cups vinegar, 4 cups sugar and 2 cups water in a large boiler pot.
Rinse vegetables and pour into vinegar mixture.
Heat until mixture comes to a boil. Simmer on low flame for 3 minutes.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal as per directions.
Makes 6 pints.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Beat together butter and peanut butter until light and fluffy.
Gradually add granulated sugar and brown sugar. Add eggs; beat well.
Add dry ingredients and blend.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Spread evenly in a well-greased and floured 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: moose salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 1 minute.

title: ice cream balls with hot pudding sauce
directions: Mix together graham cracker crumbs, sugar, cinnamon and peanut butter; set aside.
Make ice cream balls and roll in peanut butter mixture.
Place on a cookie sheet lined with wax paper.
Freeze. You can take the balls off the cookie sheet and place in containers or freezer bags until ready to use.

title: herb cheese bread
directions: Prepare dough as directed, adding basil and cheese with last addition of flour.
After kneading, shape dough into round shape. Place in well-greased 1-quart round casserole.
Turn dough over. Slash top with "x" in center.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.
(Let dough rise only once.)
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Makes 1 round loaf.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Debone chicken, cut in small pieces.
Mix soup and broth with chicken.
Melt butter; pour over stuffing mix and mix well. Grease casserole pan and put layer of chicken and layer of stuffing.
Let stuffing be on the top.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole; cover with mashed potatoes.
Top with your favorite cheese.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: pecan crunch dessert
directions: Combine sugar, pecans and egg.
Spread onto a cookie sheet that has been lined with tinfoil and greased.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and crumble.

title: crunch popcorn
directions: Mix popcorn, Rice Krispies and peanuts together.
Melt chocolate and peanut butter together.
Pour melted mixture over popcorn mix.
Put on cookie sheets sprayed with Pam.
Cool.
Break apart.
Keep in sealed containers.

title: pork chops with red onions and cranberries
directions: Pat pork chops dry and rub with thyme, salt and pepper.
Melt 2 teaspoons butter and oil in skillet over medium-high heat. Dredge chops in flour; cook until brown (2 minutes).
Transfer to plate.
Wipe out pan; add 1 stick butter and melt.
Add onion; cook until brown.
Add apple juice and boil.
Add cranberries. Put in pork.
Reduce heat and cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: sangria blanca
directions: In a glass pitcher, combine wine, Triple Sec and sugar until blended.
When ready to serve, stir in club soda and ice cubes. Garnish pitcher with fruit.
Garnish wine glasses with maraschino cherries.

title: ham and scalloped potatoes
directions: Put half of the ham, potatoes and onions in crock-pot. Sprinkle with salt, pepper and grated cheese.
Repeat with 2nd half.
Spoon undiluted soup over top.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or 4 to 5 hours on high.

title: summertime tea
directions: Boil 4 cups water and steep the tea bags for about 30 minutes. Add 3/4 cup sugar and stir to dissolve while water is hot.
Add orange juice and lemonade concentrates.
Add 8 more cups of water.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and chill.

title: pickled eggs and beets
directions: Place
juice from beets into saucepan.
Boil all ingredients together
except
eggs and beets.
Add beets; simmer a few minutes.
Cool slightly.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Mix ingredients together; roll into balls and then roll in cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with hot mustard sauce.

title: oven-barbecued ribs
directions: Cut meat into pieces.
Place in shallow pan and top with lemon slices, onion, salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: banana coffee bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Place in greased bread pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes or until done.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, combine caramels, milk and butter; cook over low heat until caramels are melted, stirring often.
Prepare cake mix according to directions; spoon half batter into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan; bake 15 minutes. Take from oven and pour melted caramel mixture over top.
Sprinkle with chips and walnuts.
Spoon remaining batter over all and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Let cool completely, then cut into bars. Tastes great topped with ice cream.

title: sweet corn fritters
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients. Beat eggs in a medium size bowl until frothy.
Add 6 tablespoons milk and all dry ingredients.
Stir and add whole kernel and creamed corn.
Batter should resemble thick pancake batter.
If too thick, beat in 1 or 2 tablespoons more of milk until desired consistency is reached. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls into deep oil (oil must be hot). Brown in about 2 minutes on both sides.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans in stock overnight.
Saute onion, mushrooms, chicken and cumin. Add beans and simmer for 3 to 4 hours, until beans are tender.
Adjust consistency with stock.
Add cream cheese and stir well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish before serving with Monterey Jack cheese.

title: sue carnes' pizza casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion, salt and pepper.
Drain off excess fat. Mix pizza sauce with macaroni and meat.
Place in a 3-quart casserole, alternating in layers with pepperoni and cheese, ending with cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple-cranberry fluff
directions: Stir together all ingredients except Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.
Just before serving, stir in Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti by directions and drain well.
Add butter.
Mix well.
Add eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Put in 10-inch pie plate and form crust.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.
Cook spaghetti sauce; pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Spread Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: mack's new york cheesecake(creamy baked cheesecake)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, melt margarine; stir in crumbs and sugar.
Pat crumbs firmly on bottom of buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool while preparing filling.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Bring to a boil the margarine, cocoa and water.
Add all other ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350°.

title: salted peanut cookies
directions: Cream sugars and shortening; add sifted flour with baking soda.
Add vanilla, eggs, cereals and salted peanuts.
Make into balls the size of a walnut.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable cheddar cheese soup
directions: Cook potatoes in water; mash into chunks (in water).
Add carrots, celery and onion; cook until tender.
Add the rest of the ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes or so.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Heat broccoli for 7 minutes.
Salt to taste.
Put in baking dish.
Put grated cheese on top of broccoli.
Pour soup over this.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
You may cover with onion rings.

title: sparkling fruit punch
directions: In a large punch bowl or container, mix all fruit juices and syrup together.
Chill until ready to serve.
Add ginger ale and mix.
Serve in a punch bowl or in glasses over ice.
Serves 25, 1/2 cup each or 12 large servings.

title: imperial chicken bake
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Dip each breast in milk; dredge in breadcrumb mixture.
Arrange in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine butter, garlic and lemon juice; drizzle over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: beef tips in gravy
directions: Cover beef tips in flour and brown in 2 tablespoons of Crisco. Cover tips with onion soup mix.
Add flour to water and pour over tips.
Let simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Can be served over rice.

title: oriental chicken pasta salad
directions: Toss one half of sesame oil with cold, cooked spaghetti.
Stir in chicken, scallions, cucumber, water chestnuts and chopped cilantro (no stems).
Set aside.

title: stuffed pistolettes
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and drain well.
Cook broccoli and drain well.
Add broccoli and cheese to meat.
Stir until cheese melts.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve jello into hot water.
Add vinegar and salt; dissolve well.
Add pineapple and carrots.
Place in decorative mold and refrigerate until set.

title: chocolate chip incredible
directions: Mix the cream, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Begin layering in a large bowl.
Begin with the whipped cream mixture, then the cookies and top with syrup.
Make 24 hours ahead and refrigerate.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff.
Gradually add sugar, while still beating.
When stiff, add chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Put in preheated oven.
Slowly count to 30.
Turn oven off.
Leave until morning.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Store in covered container. To serve, add 1 rounded teaspoon of mixture to 1 cup boiling water.
Flavor to taste with honey.
(For convenience, use honey from a plastic dispenser.)

title: knox blox
directions: In a large bowl, mix Knox unflavored gelatine with the fruit flavored gelatin.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
To serve, cut into 1-inch squares.
If you want to be real creative, you can cut them into fun shapes.
Kids love them!

title: waldorf salad(4 servings)
directions: Wash, quarter, core and pare apples, then dice.
Soak diced apples in water and lemon juice to prevent apples turning dark. Mix thoroughly with mayonnaise or yogurt.
Add sliced celery, salt and coarsely chopped English walnuts.
Toss with a fork to coat all ingredients with the mayonnaise or yogurt.
Arrange on lettuce leaves.

title: chicken-in-a-garden
directions: Combine chicken, 1 tablespoon oil, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, 1 1/2 teaspoons cornstarch, garlic powder and pepper; stir well and let stand 20 minutes.

title: lemon tea bread
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and grated lemon rind.
Add the eggs.
Sift together the flour and baking powder and add alternately with the milk.
Add the walnuts.

title: spinach salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, mix spinach, carrots, scallions and mushrooms.
In small bowl, mix oil, vinegar and mustard.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour over salad.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Shred cheese and carrots and tear broccoli florets into bite size pieces.
Mix equal amounts of shredded cheese, shredded carrots and broccoli pieces.
Add salt and pepper (as much as you desire).
Add mayonnaise to mix.
Serve cold.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in square baking pan. Sprinkle over the apples the following:
flour, sugar, beaten egg and baking powder. Drizzle 1/4 cup salad oil over this and sprinkle with cinnamon. Bake 45 minutes in a 375° oven or until top is brown.

title: banana spice drops
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Stir in bananas; measure flour and dry ingredients and nuts.
Combine with other mix. Chill for 1 hour.
Drop by teaspoon on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Combine
the
raisins,	water,	orange juice and orange marmalade.	Bring to a boil.
Mix together the sugar, salt and cloves;
stir
this
into
sauce (raisins, water, orange juice and marmalade).
Cook,
stirring
often,
until
thick.
This makes 3 cups.
Pour over cooked ham, or pour into a small bowl and pass around the table.

title: no fail custard pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 10 minutes at 400° and reduce heat to 325° until done. Makes 1 pie.

title: asparagus rollups
directions: Trim crusts from bread slices.
Flatten each slice with a rolling pin.
Mix softened butter with cheeses.
Spread cheese mixture on each bread slice and top with an asparagus spear.
Roll bread around the asparagus and dip in melted butter.
Cut each roll into 4ths and freeze.
When ready to serve, bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 96 pieces.

title: creole shrimp mold
directions: Defrost shrimp in cold water. Heat tomato soup, cut cream cheese in squares and add to soup. Add gelatin stir constantly. Add shrimp and mayonnaise. Add creole seasoning, and shallots, let cool. Pour in mold. Refrigerate over night. To remove place mold in bath of warm water and turn over on plate.

title: rosettes
directions: You will need a rosette iron.

title: gumbo jambalaya
directions: Brown chicken or pork in large pan.
Combine chopped onion, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute few minutes.
Next add uncooked rice and water and salt to taste.
Boil 20 minutes, covered.
Let stand for 10 to 15 minutes, then serve.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, eggs, cracker crumbs, onion and spices. Mix well and shape into flat rectangle (about 10 x 12-inch) on wax paper.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup of cheese onto meat mixture.
Roll up like jelly roll and pinch ends to seal.
Place in covered dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour; drain grease.
Pour tomato sauces and remaining cheese over top and bake an additional 15 minutes until lightly browned.
Slice and serve, spooning sauce over slices.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Mix broccoli, soup, mayonnaise and onion.
Sprinkle with cheese and crushed Ritz crackers or saltines.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable shepherd's pie
directions: Set mashed potatoes aside, then heat oil; saute onion, broccoli, pepper, basil and cardamon until tender and crisp.

title: hot artichoke-cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased baking dish until hot.
Serve with crackers for a dish that is "out of this world".

title: hearty hodgepodge
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, dump the pineapple chunks, juice and all.
On top of the pineapple chunks, dump pie filling of your choice.
Sprinkle with dry yellow cake mix.
Then sprinkle with pecans.
Cut butter into chunks and randomly spread on top.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes and start checking after 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Serve with chips, crackers or vegetables.

title: lemon cake
directions: Blend and beat 4 minutes all ingredients except egg whites. Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured large angel food pan. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Watch for excessive top browning near end.

title: easy orange sherbet
directions: Combine condensed milk and drinks in freezer container of a 6 quart freezer; Stirring well.
Freeze according to manufacture's instructions.
Pack Freezer.
Ripen 1 hour before serving.
Yield: 15 cups.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute bell pepper and celery.
Add remaining ingredients. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: beer batter for whatever
directions: If you forget to let the beer set out overnight to get flat, pour it into a large glass.
Sprinkle some salt in it and let stand 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar.
Add oil and beat well.
Add remainder of cake ingredients and mix well.
Add apples and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade sausage
directions: Mix all ingredients together; place in refrigerator overnight. For next three days, take from refrigerator and remix; refrigerate again.
On the fourth day, mix and shape into rolls, about 2 1/2-inches round.
Place in broiler rack with pan underneath.
Bake at 175° for 8 hours.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and freeze.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans thoroughly (about 2 times).
Remove any bad ones as well as any "junk" that floats to the top.
Drain.
Add about 6 cups of water to the beans.
Cover.
Bring to a boil 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Do not remove cover; let set for 1 hour.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Cream soup, cheese and gelatin together in a double boiler for 15 minutes.
Some pieces of cheese will not dissolve.
Add celery, onions and mayo in mixture.
Add shrimp.
Stir and blend until dissolved.
Put in mold lightly greased with mayo.
Refrigerate at least overnight or 11 hours or more.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size chunks.
Place in plastic bag.
Add other ingredients and seal bag.
Marinate for 2 hours or overnight.
Drain chicken.
Heat oil in skillet to medium-hot. Stir-fry chicken with vegetables of choice until chicken is cooked and vegetables are tender-crisp.
Mix cornstarch with cold water. Stir into chicken mixture.
Cook until thickened. Serve with cooked rice.

title: layered crab spread(makes 12 appetizer servings)
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cheese, ReaLemon brand, Worcestershire and garlic powder until fluffy; stir in onion.
On serving plate, spread cheese mixture into 6-inch circle.
Top with chili sauce then crab meat.
Cover; chill.
Serve with crackers. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: orange fluff
directions: Stir gelatin and hot water until well dissolved. Spoon in sherbet. Stir until gelatin thickens and sherbet is melted.
Pour into bowl or individual glass dishes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows and spread with whipped topping.

title: roasted pecans
directions: Soak for 3 hours. Drain and bake on low, stirring often.

title: easy sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Roll into balls about the size of a walnut. Press with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: dixie potatoes
directions: Peel and slice boiled sweet potatoes and arrange in baking dish.
Cover with generous portion of brown sugar with slices of butter scattered on top.
Sprinkle on the cinnamon, then add the milk.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onions, pepper and celery in skillet. Add pimentos, peas, mushroom, tomato soup, salt and pepper. Alternate this mixture with noodles in 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, Sprinkle grated cheese over top for last 15 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: Stir cornmeal and salt into boiling water.
Cook stirring constantly until thick.
Continue cooking over very low heat 5 more minutes, stirring continually.
Spread 2/3 of the cooked cornmeal on bottom and sides of a deep baking dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour into dish.
Spread remaining cornmeal over the top of the mixture.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix well.
Place sticks in the ends of 6 hotdog wieners. Drop into hot deep fat (350°).
Cook until golden brown.
Serve hot with mustard or ketchup.

title: dutch baby pancakes
directions: Once you decide on a pan, measure its total volume by pouring in quarts of water.
When you've determined the pan's volume, select the recipe proportions you need from the preceding list. Get out the ingredients and you're ready to start.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix and beat all ingredients and pour into a large Pyrex dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Or put in three 8-inch layer cake pans and bake 30 minutes or a Bundt pan and bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Test center with toothpick.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Stir in cream cheese and put in refrigerator until jello begins to thicken.
Whip with mixer. Fold in pineapple and pecans.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: mushrooms and chicken wings
directions: Brown wings in margarine.
Remove from pan.
Saute onions and garlic until soft.
Stir in mushrooms.
Saute lightly.
Add water, salt, rosemary and chicken wings.
Cover and simmer 20 to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: broccoli fettucine
directions: In a skillet, lightly brown chicken breasts and season with salt and pepper.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Cover with cream of chicken soup, 1 can milk and 2 cans water.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramel pie
directions: Boil 1 can condensed milk for 3 hours, in the can!.
Do not open first.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip. Ready to serve.
Caramel can be made days ahead of time.

title: raisin cake
directions: Boil raisins in water for 10 minutes.
Add soda and lard; let cool.
Sift flour with salt, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg and baking powder.
Beat eggs; add sugar and milk.
Add flour and raisin mixture.
Cook in tube pan at 350° for an hour or more (until done).

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine macaroni, water, butter, onion and salt in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cover.
Cook on High 5 minutes, then Low 5 minutes.
Stir twice during cooking.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Cook on High 12 to 15 minutes or until macaroni is tender and sauce is thickened and bubbly, stirring every 3 minutes.

title: scalloped cheese potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Slice thin 3 potatoes into greased casserole bowl.
Layer 4 slices of cheese, salt and pepper.
Repeat potato and cheese layers.
Pour approximately 1/2 to 3/4 cup of milk over casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: lemony asparagus and new potatoes
directions: Heat grill.
Cut 14-inch square sheet of heavy-duty foil. Break or cut off tough ends of asparagus.
Cut spears into 1 1/2 to 2-inch pieces.
Place asparagus and potatoes in center of foil. Sprinkle with salt and thyme.
In small bowl, combine margarine and lemon peel.
Blend well.
Drizzle over vegetables.
Stir gently to coat.
Wrap and seal securely with tight double folds.
Place foil packet on gas grill over medium heat on on charcoal grill 4 to 6-inches from medium-high coals.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Open packet.
Stir gently.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: cold veggie pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls in a 9 X 13-inch pan, or pizza pan. Bake until done as indicated on can.
Cool.

title: rose geranium sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt; add grated rind.
Add this to first mixture gradually, alternating with milk or juice.
Add 1 tablespoon anise seed, crushed or whole, and geranium leaves.
Chill dough.
Roll out thinly on a floured board.
Cut with cutter dipped in flour.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
For drop cookies add more liquid and drop from teaspoons.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk.
Stir in tuna and add peas.
Crush potato chips in mixture.
Put 1/4 cup potato chips on top.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, chilies and onion together.
Spread on each tortilla and roll tightly.
Each can be cut into bite size.
Serve picante sauce on the side for dipping tortilla.
May freeze until ready to use.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Blend gently all ingredients. Be sure to use all of juice from fruit cocktail. Pour into ungreased oblong pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: bake macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook and drain macaroni.
Fry beef and drain.
Cut tomatoes and add lightly fried onion.
Cut up cheese in cubes.
Add macaroni, beef, onion and tomatoes.
Mix 1/2 cheese in mixture and the rest on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Mix everything except cheese together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour covered.
Uncover for last 5 minutes; top with cheese.

title: texas tumbleweed dip(microwave)
directions: Using a 1-quart casserole, cook broccoli in microwave.
Spread it out on paper towel to drain (or drain in a fine mesh colander). In same casserole dish, place butter, mushrooms, onion and celery.
Microwave until vegetables are tender.
Stir in broccoli, soup and cheese.
Continue to microwave, stirring occasionally, until cheese is melted and hot.
Pour into a chafing dish; serve with chips for dipping.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter cake pan with 1/4 stick of butter.
Place pie filling in pan.
Smooth out.
Put pineapple with juice next.
Empty dry cake mix on top.
Slice butter very thin so that it covers all of cake.
Juices will bubble up to cook dry cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli cheddar rolls
directions: Let
dough thaw until
pliable.
On
a
lightly
floured board, roll dough out to a 12-inch square.
Combine all remaining ingredients except butter in
a small bowl.
Spread filling mixture over dough.
Roll up
tightly
in
a jelly roll.
Pinch dough along edge to seal filling
in.
Slice
roll in 8 pieces. Cut each slice in half again,
not cutting all the way through. Fan out sides to form butterfly shaped rolls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet and brush
with
butter.
Let
rise for 45 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: crustless hot fudge pie
directions: Mix cocoa, vanilla and butter.
Mix sugar, flour and salt. Add chocolate and blend.
Beat in eggs and pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: egg pie
directions: Beat egg and egg yolks together; add sugar with 1 tablespoon flour in the sugar.
Add milk and stir well.
Pour into crust and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Put in oven until done.
Bake at 350°.

title: sweet potato and pineapple casserole
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, combine sweet potatoes, pineapple and molasses.
Combine cracker crumbs, margarine and ginger root until well blended.
Sprinkle evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing mixture over butter; add a layer of chicken.
Slice boiled eggs over chicken; add rest of stuffing mix.
Combine soups and broth.
Mix well and pour over entire mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat
the
eggs until light.
Add to grated sweet potatoes. Gradually add sugar.
Stir in milk and rest of ingredients.
Place the pudding in a greased baking dish.
Bake in a moderate	oven at	350°
for
about 1/2 hour.
Stir it with a spoon.
Bake
it 15	minutes
longer.
Serve
it with whipped cream, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: japanese fruit pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2.

title: applesauce-spice squares
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add egg, beating well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and pumpkin pie spice; add to creamed mixture alternately with applesauce, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from oven; cool.
Spread with Browned Butter Frosting.
Cut into squares to serve.
Yields 9 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift first 6 ingredients together, then add all the rest.
Mix until moistened; beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan about 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool. Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: strawberry jello salad with sour cream
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot water. Add pineapple (juice and fruit), mashed bananas, strawberries and nuts. Pour half of mixture into a dish (9 x 13-inches) and firmly chill. Spread sour cream on firm Jell-O. Top with remaining Jell-O mixture and chill until firm. Serves 12.

title: keith's sausage and ziti
directions: Cook sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic until meat is brown and vegetables tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, 1/2 cup water, salt, pepper and oregano.
Stir in cooked ziti.
Turn half the ziti mixture into 2-quart baking dish. Top with half cheese.
Add remaining ziti mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Heat 5 minutes more. Serves 6 to 8.

title: devils food cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients. In separate bowl, mix shortening, milk, and flavoring; add in the dry mixture and mix well. Beat in the eggs; pour into 2 greased and floured pans and bake at 350° until done.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over quick oats.
Mix.
Let stand 20 minutes in a bowl.
Cream butter, brown sugar and white sugar. Beat 2 eggs until foamy and combine.
Then add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add this mixture to oats.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: old time apple cake
directions: In a large bowl, sprinkle sugar over apples.
Let stand 30 minutes or until juicy.
Stir in eggs, flour, baking soda, cinnamon and 3 tablespoons wheat germ until well blended.
Turn into 8-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle with remaining wheat germ.
Bake in 375° oven 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack or serve warm.

title: chicken parmesan with mushroom marsala sauce
directions: Pour olive oil in center of a 12-inch frying pan.
Place pats of butter around oil.
Heat slowly to cooking temperature. Combine bread crumbs and cheese. Wash and pat dry the chicken. Coat with seasoned flour.
Dip in eggs.
Coat with seasoned bread crumb mixture. Set aside on waxed paper or rack.
Repeat for all pieces. Let stand in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.
Place all pieces in frying pan at the same time; fry to golden brown.
Pour sauce over chicken just before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mrs. v chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together oleo, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; stir into first mixture. Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake until light brown.
Cookie will be soft.
Bake at 375° about 8 minutes.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Mix together sugars and corn syrup.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, cornflakes and peanuts.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan; drizzle melted chocolate chips over the top.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: Layer 1:
Spread in oblong glass dish:
beans and taco mix (mixed well).

title: fruit 'n yogurt salad
directions: In small saucepan over medium heat, cook pineapple and orange syrups with cornstarch, stirring constantly, until thickened. Cool slightly.
In a large bowl, combine yogurt, sugar and vanilla.
Add cooled mixture.
Stir in pineapple, orange segments, grapes, bananas and apple.
Cover; refrigerate 4 hours or until completely chilled.
Makes twelve 1/2-cup servings.

title: mexican luncheon dish
directions: Saute sausage in skillet until brown; drain off excess drippings.
Add onions, jalapeno peppers and green pepper.
Saute until onion is transparent.
Add macaroni, tomatoes, sour cream, milk, sugar, chili powder and salt.
Cover.
Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until macaroni is tender.
Yields about 8 servings.

title: fiesta zucchini coleslaw
directions: Drain shredded zucchini by gently pressing between layers of paper towel.
Combine zucchini and next four ingredients.
Set aside.
Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Add to zucchini mixture and toss gently.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour. Serves 6.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Pull chicken apart in small pieces. Mix soups, Ro-Tel and broth; mix well.
Cover bottom of casserole dish with crushed Doritos.
Layer 1 cup chicken, half of onions, half of soup mixture and half of cheese.
Repeat layers and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix sugar-free jello (dry) with oranges, pineapple, bananas and strawberries.
Mix pie filling with all ingredients and keep in the refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions and drain.
Mix all ingredients together in order given and put in a 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix well and roll in crushed nuts, if desired.
Makes 2 cheese balls.

title: jess's chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan. Sprinkle with teriyaki sauce and rub into chicken.
Season with garlic powder, parsley flakes, salt and pepper.
Cover with foil; bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes before serving.
Brush butter onto chicken and bake, uncovered, for remaining 20 minutes.

title: whiskey slush
directions: Mix and put in freezer for 3 days.
Stir 2 times a day.
Mix slush mix with 7-Up.
Serve.

title: crab ala king
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Saute green pepper and pimento until tender.
Add flour and blend thoroughly.
Add milk, cook and stir until thick.
Add crab meat, salt and pepper and heat thoroughly.
Stir in beaten egg yolks until well blended.
Serve over hot rice.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Stir all ingredients until well blended.
To serve, add 1/4 cup chocolate mix to 2/3 cup hot water.
Yield:
3 quarts dry mix.

title: ham pie
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
