Stir in flour; add soup and milk and heat until thickened.
Add ham and lemon juice; mix well and pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Roll out 4 to 5 biscuits flat and cut out centers with a small cutter.
Arrange large pieces on top of ham mixture; fill in between large biscuits with small center pieces of biscuit.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Reduce to 350° and cook until biscuits are done.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into two frozen pie crusts. Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate candy
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Melt in double boiler 1/3 to 1/2 block paraffin wax, 1 large package chocolate chips and 1 large package milk chocolate chips.
Take out preparation and roll into walnut-sized balls. Dip candy into chocolate mixture and place on wax paper.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well; refrigerate.
Good with green apples, melon, strawberries and green grapes.

title: country fried steak and gravy
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Put flour, salt and pepper in plastic bag.
Coat steak pieces with flour mixture and brown on both sides in
hot oil, about 10 minutes.
Remove from skillet and place in baking dish.
Make gravy and pour over steak in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tasty baked beans
directions: Mix all
together.
Bake at 350° for approximately 2 to 3 hours.
Make
sure to add enough water to cover beans before baking.
Do not overbake.

title: egg noodles or spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and rest of ingredients, except sour cream and cheese and noodles. Simmer 30 minutes.
Boil the noodles (I prefer) or spaghetti until done. Drain.
Add the sour cream.
Place in layers in a casserole, first the noodles, meat sauce, cheese, etc., ending with cheese on top. Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: hot chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine chicken, rice, onion, celery, eggs, soup, lemon juice, pickles and mayonnaise in bowl; mix well.
Spoon into baking dish. Chill overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes. Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: peanut butter chip chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chips.
Chill until firm enough to handle.
Shape small amount of dough into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: meatballs, italian style
directions: Mix all ingredients, except tomatoes.
Brown the meatballs in oil.
Pour 1/2 tomatoes on bottom of casserole.
Lay meatballs on top of the tomatoes.
Pour the remaining tomatoes on top.
Cover with foil and bake 40 minutes at 350°, or cook on top of the stove in your own sauce for about 2 hours.

title: 3 bean casserole
directions: Leave beans in juice. Fry bacon. Brown hamburger.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash, peel and grate potatoes on coarse blade of 4 sided grater (you can grate with skins on and may like it better).
In a medium bowl, lightly beat the eggs and add all else.
Grease a large nonstick skillet with oil and heat over medium-high heat.
Spoon heaping tablespoon of the mixture onto the skillet and flatten with a spatula.
Cook until golden brown on one side about 2 to 3 minutes, then turn over and do the same on the other side.
Drain on paper toweling and serve quickly with apple sauce.
Makes 12 to 16 pancakes.

title: kiss pudding
directions: Scald milk.
Beat egg yolks and add sugar, salt and cornstarch which has been made into a smooth paste by adding a little milk. Add this mixture to the scalded milk.
Cook until thick.
When cool, add flavoring.
Serve with topping.

title: meal in foil
directions: Sprinkle meat with tenderizer to package directions; season according to taste.
Place seasoned meat in center of large piece of foil.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix and steak sauce.
Top with carrots, celery and potatoes.
Dot vegetables with butter and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fold over all and seal.
Bake at 400° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: meatballs (italian)
directions: Soak bread crumbled in milk for 1/2 hour or so. Mix beef, salt, pepper, eggs, bread crumbs, garlic, parsley flakes and Parmesan cheese until well blended. Add bread that has been soaking. Mix and shape into meatballs.

title: crab maryland
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add crab and heat thoroughly. Sprinkle with flour and seasoning. Add cream and toss lightly. Add mushrooms.
Just before serving, add 1 or 2 tablespoons sherry. (Can substitute lobster or shrimp.) Serve over toast or rice.

title: stir-fry(low-fat)
directions: Coat stir-fry pan or large frying pan with 1/2 teaspoon of oil or Pam.
Stir-fry meat over medium heat until done.
Remove meat to platter.
Add remaining oil.
Stir-fry sliced vegetables for about 2 minutes.
Add spices and brown sugar.
Toss to coat vegetables.
Cook for another 2 minutes.
Add soy sauce and return meat to pan.
Cook all ingredients one more minute, tossing frequently.
Serves 2.

title: venison steak in gravy
directions: Tenderize the venison with a tenderizing hammer.
Roll steaks in flour; salt and pepper to taste.
In a large iron skillet, place about 1/4 cup of shortening and fry steaks until well done on both sides.
Remove steaks and add a little flour to the drippings in the skillet; brown, stirring constantly.
Add a little canned milk.
Stir constantly.
Make a runny gravy from this, then add the steaks back into this gravy.
Simmer for 15 minutes or longer, checking to make sure the gravy doesn't get too thick.
If it does start to get too thick, add water as needed. The longer the venison simmers in this gravy, the more the "wild" taste disappears.
Simmer to desired tenderness.

title: hawaiian bread and dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.	Remove center of bread and break the center into small pieces and place around loaf on outside of plate.
Put dip in the hole of the center of bread.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream
margarine
and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add
flour;
mix
well.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Roll out dough
on
lightly
floured surface to 1/8 inch thickness. Cut into
desired
shapes with cookie cutter.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: breakfast ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly butter a 9-inch tube or Bundt pan. Mix ingredients well; pack into pan.
Bake for 20 minutes. Remove from oven; drain off fat.
Return to oven; bake 20 minutes more.
Turn onto heated platter; fill center with scrambled eggs. May be served with country fried or hash brown potatoes.

title: all american hot dish
directions: Cook noodles.
drain; set aside.
Cook beef in skillet.
Add onions.
Stir in corn with liquid.
Add remaining ingredients including noodles.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove, cover and cook for 10 minutes.
Let stand for 10 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Bake rolls flat as directed. Let cool. Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and dry Ranch packet. Spread over crust. Top with cut veggies and cheese.

title: chicken broccoli dinner
directions: Mix together soup, lemon, curry, Miracle Whip, Mrs. Dash and place aside.
Cook broccoli and chicken, cut up and mix together in deep pan (12 x 14-inch).
Pour sauce over chicken and broccoli. Cover with grated cheese then croutons on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 375 degrees for 1 hour or until soft.
Allow to cool.
Cut a thin slice off the top of each potato.
Scoop out the pulp and place in a bowl;
add butter and mash the pulp. Blend in milk, bacon, onion, chives, salt, pepper and 1 cup of cheese.
Spoon into potato shells.
Top with remaining cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Place on a baking sheet.
Bake, uncovered, at 375 degrees for 25-30 minutes or until heated through.

title: marinated steaks
directions: Mix dressing, onion, tomato, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic with water in a Ziploc bag.
Close bag and mix well. Place steaks in bag and close.
Place plastic Ziploc bag in fridge overnight or in early A.M.
Turn every few hours.
When ready to cook, remove meat from bag and drain.
Place steaks on roasting pan.
Roast in oven until desired browning.
Watch closely and turn often.

title: ham and broccoli quiche
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: diet barbecue chicken
directions: Cook first 3 items in oleo 5 minutes.
Don't brown.
Add remaining ingredients except chicken and bring to a boil.
Add chicken.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes until chicken is tender. Good served with mashed potatoes.

title: sugar cookies(these are soft cake like cookies.)
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time; beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla and baking soda in vinegar to milk.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to creamed sugar mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 375°. Bake cookies 10 to 12 minutes.
When cool, ice cookies.

title: savory southwest spoon bread
directions: In a 4 to 6-quart pan, pour milk, butter, sugar and salt. Heat mixture over medium heat until steaming.
Add corn meal while stirring constantly.
Cook until thick, 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand.
Separate eggs.
Beat into corn meal 6 egg yolks.
Let stand while next step is prepared.
Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff.
Blend 1 cup egg whites with corn meal mixture.
Add chicken, chiles and remaining egg whites.
Fold together.
Pour into buttered 3-quart casserole. Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve immediately with salsa.

title: whole-grain crunch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 370°.
Beat together butter, sugars, egg, milk and vanilla.
Add the combined flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix well.
Add oats, wheat germ and nuts.
Mix.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 4 to 4 1/2 dozen.

title: jiffy hash pastry
directions: Cook onions and potatoes, then remove from pan.
Scramble and cook hamburger meat, then mix onions and potatoes with the hamburger meat.
Place mixture in one pie shell.
Cover with second pie shell and seal the edges.
Do not slash.
Brush on a mixture of egg and water.
Place on cookie sheet in middle of oven.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tabasco-roquefort french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in covered jar; shake well before using.
Makes 1 1/4 cups dressing.
Wonderful on mixed greens, tomatoes and cucumbers or potato salad.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Stir sugar and cocoa in a large glass bowl.
Stir in butter and marshmallows.
Place bowl in microwave.
Cook on full power for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add milk and nuts.
Beat well.
Return to microwave and cook for 30 to 60 seconds on full power.
Pour into buttered dish; chill and then cut.

title: kids fruit dip
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese with a mixer for about 3 minutes.
Chill and serve with your favorite fruit.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook chicken; keep broth.
Cook celery and onions in butter; add chicken broth and simmer 15 minutes.
Add slowly to cheese and soup. Next, add cooked noodles. Let stand 1 hour or longer.
Add cut up chicken, spices and olives.
Put in 9 x 15-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Add more grated cheese if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Saute beef, onion and season salt in a 10-inch skillet until beef loses its redness.
Drain off fat.
Add seasonings, Manwich and water.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
In 2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce and cheese.
Continue until all is used, ending with cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: wasetti
directions: Brown meat in butter. Add both soups and bring to a simmer. Add cheese and cook until cheese is melted. Cook noodles by package directions. Mix noodles and meat mixture in large pan. Add salt and pepper to taste. Pour into baking dish and cover with grated cheese. Bake at 400° until it bubbles.

title: sweet pickle peaches
directions: Blanch peaches 1 minute in boiling water; put into cold water to cool, then peel.
Make syrup by boiling 2 cups of sugar, water, vinegar and spices for 3 minutes.
Add remainder and cook until tender.
Cover and let stand for a day.
Drain off syrup and reheat.
Pack peaches in hot jars; cover with hot syrup.
Process 15 minutes below boiling (188°), then seal.

title: honey whole-wheat bread
directions: Put shortening, honey and salt in the hot milk.
Let set until cool. Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
In large bowl, combine white and whole-wheat flour.
Mix some flour (1/2 to 1 cup) with yeast. After the yeast has risen, add the milk mixture. Stir until well blended.
Mix in the rest of the flour.

I have found the best way to work bread dough is to pour out onto work table and roll, folding in the ends as your roll grows longer. Work it this way until all at once it will feel soft and springy. Put into greased bowl.
Cover.
Let rise until dough "falls" when touched in the middle.
The recipe says to let rise only once. First time you work it down, you shape it into loaves.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: mile branch homemade cane syrup
directions: The specialty of the general store is delicious hoop cheese and crackers.
The cheese is sliced while you watch and is sliced with an old fashioned hand slicer.
Also available in the store are sugar cookies, cane juice, lemonade and
Mile Branch syrup.

title: black joe cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, coffee, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all and chill.
Serve on spinach leaves or lettuce.

title: chocolate sodas
directions: Blend 1/2 quart dry milk, 14 ounces club soda, 1/4 pound chocolate and 1/4 gallon chocolate ice cream on whip, then do the other half of the ingredients to make the complete serving size.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Beat sugar and margarine until creamy.
Add eggs and cocoa. Beat until smooth.
Add salt, vanilla and flour.
Again beat until smooth.
Fold in 3/4 cup nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
While hot, spread with small marshmallows and 1/4 cup of nuts.
Let cool and frost.

title: summer coconut cream pie
directions: Put filling and coconut into bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into crust.
Sprinkle with more coconut on top. Chill until serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut bread into fourths.
Put half of bread in bottom of casserole dish.
Layer half of sausage-egg mixture and cheese over bread.
Make second layer of each.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in baking dish. Refrigerate until jello sets.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream 3/4 cup sugar and butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Stir in mixture of flour, salt, baking soda and cream of tartar.
In another bowl, combine 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Chill dough to form balls easily.
Shape dough in 1-inch balls and roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: heaven salad
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients just to a boil, cool.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water.
Pour pineapple mixture into water and gelatin mixture.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese.
Add to mixture when cool.
Add whipping cream (whipped).
Fold in mini marshmallows and sliced bananas.
Chill in refrigerator.
Best served same day.

title: shrimp in garlic
directions: Cut the shrimp in half lengthwise.
Mix all the ingredients, except margarine, together.
Marinate the shrimp for 3 hours in this mixture.
In large skillet, melt margarine over low heat. Add shrimp and marinade seasonings.
Simmer until lightly browned. Serve over rice.
Serves 2.

title: corned beef goodies
directions: Divide dough into 3 pieces and roll each piece into a 5 inch circle.
Mix egg and water in a small bowl.
Moisten edges of dough circles with egg mixture.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Sift together baking powder, salt and flour.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Beat egg whites; fold into batter.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.

title: taste treat chili
directions: Brown the beef and sausage in large dutch oven; add onions and garlic, stirring for about 1 minute.
Drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except for the kidney beans, slivered almonds and toppings.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Add kidney beans and almonds, heat through. Serve hot with corn chips, Nacho chips, crackers or cornbread and your favorite toppings.

title: hamlin's white dip
directions: Mix all together and let set for 24 hours before serving.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain well.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, mushrooms, onion and garlic salt and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles, using salt and vegetable oil.
Drain well.
Layer half of the noodles, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, then repeat layers.
Bake at 325° until hot all the way through.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking soda; set aside.
Cream peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Add honey (I use 1/2 cup honey and 1/2 cup molasses) and sugar, beating well after each addition.
Then add well beaten eggs.
Mix well; then add the sifted flour.
Drop on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Check bottom, it burns easily.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cut butter into cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into greased oblong pan.
Build up edges and bake 10 minutes.
Arrange apples on warm crust.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Blend sour cream and egg, then drizzle over apples.
Bake 25 minutes and serve warm.

title: cranberry-orange preserves(microwave)
directions: In a 2-quart microwavable bowl, combine sugar and sauce from whole cranberries; mix well.
Microwave on High 8 to 10 minutes or until mixture comes to a full boil.
Add orange slices.
Microwave on High 7 to 8 minutes or until orange peels are tender.
Add cranberries, pectin and cinnamon sticks.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High 5 to 7 minutes or until mixture thickens.
Stir well and pour into sterilized jars.
Seal.

title: honey-apple pancakes
directions: In a bowl, mix the first 5 ingredients.
In another bowl, mix the remaining ingredients.
Add the liquid mixture to the flour mixture, blending until slightly lumpy.

title: low-fat chili
directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick cooking spray; brown the meat.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer until the chili has thickened.
Serve.
This will serve 8 people; 160 calories and 2 grams of fat per serving.

title: squaw corn
directions: Mix and layer in greased 8 x 12-inch Pyrex dish with 1/2 pound grated Cheddar cheese and 1 can green chilies.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lena's chicken salad
directions: This is good for low calorie and fat grams.

title: old-fashioned chicken pastry
directions: Bring salt, pepper and water to a rolling boil in a large stockpot. Add chicken and bring to boil again. Turn heat back to low; cover with lid and cook chicken until tender (1 to 2 hours). Remove chicken from pot and let cool enough to be able to pull it off the bones. Return chicken to pot and simmer on low heat.

title: asparagus ham rolls
directions: Separate ham slices and lay on a flat surface.
Cut each cheese slice in half, crosswise and lay atop each ham slice.
Top each with 2 to 3 asparagus spears.
Roll and place in a single layer, seam side down, in a 2-quart dish.
Combine soup, water and celery salt.
Spoon evenly over ham rolls and cover.
Cook on High, 5 to 7 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds and serve.

title: cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat together cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Turn into crust and bake 35 minutes. Remove from oven and spread sour cream on top.
Return to oven for 5 minutes.
Chill and serve plain or with fruit.
Strawberries or blueberries are great.

title: broccoli three cheese bake
directions: Saute onions and garlic for 8 minutes.
In 8-inch square baking dish mix onions, pasta, broccoli, Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan, basil, salt and oregano.
In separate bowl, beat milk and eggs; add to baking dish.
Top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: engagement salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple and sour cream.
Fold in marshmallows, cherries and nuts.
Pour into individual molds. Refrigerate.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: old fashion pound cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Mix sugar and egg yolks together.
Set aside. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Then add egg yolks and sugar mixture to egg whites.
Keep beating all the time.
Add flour, beating all the time.
Add melted margarine, still beating.
Beat well.
Put in well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: soldiers kisses
directions: Beat eggs until stiff and stands in peaks.
Add brown sugar; mix slowly.
Fold in pecans, then add vanilla and salt.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Stores a long while if kept in a tin.

title: hard times cake
directions: * Do not use self-rising flour.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and eggs. Cook pudding according to directions. Add hot pudding to mix slowly and stir well. Pour into floured and greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with nuts and chips and bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: frozen virgin banana daiquiri
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Blend on high until thick and creamy.
Pour into tall glasses.
Makes 4 servings, 6 ounces each. Calories per serving:
Diabetic exchange:
2 fruit.

title: grandma's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt in bowl.
Add eggs, stirring just enough to break them up.
Add buttermilk and vanilla; stir until just blended.
Add melted butter; stir slightly and quickly.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until centers are set.
Cool thoroughly before cutting.

title: golden chiffon cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Make a well and add in order salad oil, egg yolks, water, lemon rind and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until smooth.
Place egg whites and cream of tartar in large mixing bowl.
Whip until whites form extra stiff peaks.
(Do not underbeat.)

title: orange salad
directions: Sprinkle
jello over cottage cheese.
Add pineapple and orange slices.
Fold
in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in two layers.
Place one layer in bottom of punch bowl.
Poke holes in cake.
Mix pudding as directed and pour half over cake in bowl.
Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Put in strawberries.
Pour 1/2 over first layer.
Cover with Cool Whip. Place second layer of cake in bowl and repeat.

title: banana nut bundt cake
directions: Cream oleo until fluffy.
Add sugar and eggs; stir.
Add vanilla, bananas, salt, soda and flour; stir.
Add nuts.
This will be very thick.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Spoon in mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Check at 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken creole
directions: Brown chicken in oil until done.
Saute onion and green pepper along with chicken.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: turkey burgers
directions: Blend all ingredients together with hands. Cover and chill at least 1 hour, or up to 4 hours. Makes 4 patties. Grill 4-5 minutes on each side.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Brown the chopped onion in 2 tablespoons butter, then mix all other ingredients and cook for 1/2 hour over medium or medium-low heat.

title: easy orange butternut squash
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in casserole dish (about 3-quart) and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: manchupa(samp & beans)
directions: Rinse out samp.
Place samp in a 12 quart pot half filled with water and bay leaf.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down and let simmer for 1 hour.
Add kale, linguicia, short ribs, and salt.
Saute onions in oil.
Add paprika and black pepper to onions.
Add onion mixture to pot; add enough water to cover the vegetables.
Bring pot up to a boil; lower heat and allow pot to simmer for at least 3 1/2 -4 hours.
During the last 1/2 hour of cooking add cans of butter beans (Juice and all).

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook spaghetti and put in bowl.
Stir in margarine, egg and Parmesan cheese.
Arrange spaghetti on bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan.
Spread with Ricotta or cottage cheese.
Spoon on meat sauce.
Add layer Mozzarella cheese and another layer meat sauce.
Bake 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and bake another 10 minutes.

title: cream pull candy
directions: Let sugars and water boil to 240°. Add margarine at 240°and let boil to 260°. Add vanilla. Pour on cold marble board and start pulling until taffy-like, then cut. Takes a few days for candy to get creamy.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Put bread crumbs on top. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: spiced cranberry-orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in a large bowl. Stir in cranberry sauce; add cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Stir in oranges and walnuts.
Spoon into a 5-cup ring mold.
Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm.
Unmold and garnish as desired.
Makes about 5 cups.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well all of the ingredients except for the marshmallows. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with marshmallows.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine soup, milk, seasoned salt, chicken and thawed vegetables (if in a hurry, cook vegetables until almost done in about 1/4 cup water; drain and add to preceding mixture).
Add 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup onions.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; bake, covered, in a 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, cinnamon and salt; add to first four ingredients.
Mix 3 cups fresh, diced apples into ingredients.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° in tube pan.

title: karen's bacon crisps
directions: Wrap each cracker with a half strip of bacon. Place on a cookie/cake cooling rack over a shallow drip pan/baking sheet. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, turning once. Serve hot. Makes 24.

title: scotchies
directions: Melt butter.
Add eggs and blend.
Stir in vanilla, flour, baking powder, brown sugar and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and applesauce; beat well.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with water.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts, chopped, and 1 cup raisins.
Pour into 3 greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Or bake in tube pan for 1 hour.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Dip chicken breasts in melted butter (enough to cover) and roll in flour.
Place in a baking dish and bake at 325° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Take out and turn chicken.
Bake for 15 minutes more.
Take from oven.
Pour soup, milk and cheese mixture over breasts.
Return to the oven for 15 minutes.

title: fractured tacos
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning mix as directed.
In large casserole dish, crush chips to fit in bottom of dish.
Layer meat mixture, beans, sour cream, lettuce, cheese and tomatoes.
Serve.
This can be made ahead by cooking meat ahead and putting together just before serving.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms, chop into 1/4 inch pieces.
Set aside.
Heat butter in heavy skillet, add mushrooms caps.
Saute quickly over high heat for 30 seconds on each side or until just browned.

title: mushroom meatballs
directions: Blend mushroom soup with 1/2 cup water.
Measure out 1/4 cup soup mixture and combine with ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, parsley, egg and salt.
Shape into meatballs, about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Brown in 1 tablespoon of shortening in large skillet. Add remaining soup mixture; cover and cook over low heat about 15 minutes; stir occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: bubble biscuits
directions: Cut biscuits into
1/4	shapes.
Put sugar and cinnamon into a plastic bag;
add
biscuits
and
shake to coat.
Place into a greased cake
or Bundt pan.
Combine the following 1 to 2 minutes and
pour
over
biscuits:	sugar, oleo or margarine and corn syrup.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli completely; drain.
Mix egg, soup, sour cream, salt, pepper and onion.
Add to broccoli in casserole.
Top with grated cheese and crushed soda crackers.
Cook in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Double recipe for a crowd.

title: nacho chicken
directions: Crush enough tortilla chips to cover bottom of medium casserole dish.
Parboil chicken, cut into cubes, layer on top of chips.
Mix tomatoes, cream of chicken and cream of mushroom soups.
Pour over chicken.
Shred or slice Velveeta, about 1/2 package, and sprinkle over top.
Add more crushed chips to top, bake at 350° for 1/2 hour, until cheese is melted and dish is warmed through.

title: kat's peanut butter pie
directions: Using a fork, mix sugar and peanut butter until little balls are formed.
Mix Jell-O pie filling as directed.
Spread a heaping tablespoonful of pie (chocolate) filling, then a layer of peanut butter balls (1/2 of mixture).
Fill the rest with pie filling and top with Cool Whip and chill for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin cheesecake bars
directions: Combine flour and brown sugar in medium bowl.
Cut in butter to make a crumb mix.
Stir in nuts.
Set aside 3/4 cup for topping. Press remaining mix into bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, pumpkin, eggs, spices and vanilla in bowl.
Blend until smooth.
Pour over baked crust.
Sprinkle with reserved topping.
Bake additional 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting into bars.

title: pinwheels
directions: Soften
cream cheese to room temperature.
Separate ham slices on individual pieces of waxed paper and wipe with paper towel. Separate
cream
cheese
into
portions
and spread carefully and
evenly
on
ham
slices.
Line 5 to 6 olives at narrow end of ham.
Firmly roll up pinwheel style and wrap in foil.

title: ojaldas (fried cakes)
directions: Sift flour and salt together.
Blend the flour into the eggs. Knead ten minutes, adding more flour if needed to make stiff dough.
Let the dough stand one hour.
Roll very thin and cut into diamond shapes.
Fry in hot oil.
Drain and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pastas until desired doneness.
When stirring in your dressing, estimate the amount you desire.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together sugar, margarine, shortening and eggs.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Shape dough (it will be stiff) by rounded teaspoonfuls in balls.

title: missy potatoes
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients. Spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs evenly over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: susie's antipasta rice salad
directions: Cook rice and let cool.
Add next 6 ingredients; toss together.
Add salad dressing and mushrooms.
Makes 4 main dishes.

title: chicken curry rolls
directions: Trim crusts from bread slices.
Roll bread lightly with rolling pin to flatten slightly.
Combine chicken, onion, mayonnaise and salt.
Spread filling over bread.
Roll up each slice like a jelly roll.
Heat butter with curry powder until melted.
Brush over rolls.
Arrange rolls in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 475° about 10 minutes, until rich golden brown.
Serve hot.
Untoasted rolls may be covered with foil and stored in refrigerator for later use.

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir well.
Add one medium Cool Whip and stir well.
Add 1 can Mandarin oranges and 2 or 3 bananas, sliced.
Add shredded coconut, if desired.

title: pork chops neapolitan style
directions: Roast peppers in hot oven.
Peel and cut into strips.
Slice mushrooms.
Put olive oil in skillet and brown garlic in it. Remove garlic and place chops in skillet.
Brown slowly on both sides, adding salt and pepper.
Remove chops from pan and keep warm.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together oleo and cheese.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add sugar.
Spread between layers and on top.
Sprinkle nuts between layers and on top.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Roll out dough; cut in strips.
Dry and cook.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popped popcorn in 2 large roasting pans.
Sprinkle almonds or nuts over popcorn.
Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to boil and continue to boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popcorn and mix well. Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Put into Tupperware immediately so it won't stick to pans.

title: powdered sugar
directions: Blend in blender for 2 minutes.

title: tropical squash
directions: Boil squash until tender. Whip squash until smooth.
Add sugar and orange juice and whip until blended.
More or less orange juice may be used according to the dryness of the squash.
Serves 4.

title: beef stir-fry
directions: Slice beef into very thin strips.
Mix cornstarch, broth and soy.

title: greta's easy lemon pie
directions: Mix milk and lemonade, then fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into vanilla wafer crust.
Chill overnight.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Tear bread into small pieces and sprinkle over butter.
Sprinkle sausage over bread crumbs.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs and other ingredients; pour over mixture.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: You may use a food processor to mince whole cranberries and later the peeled and cored apple using the mince blade.
Combine minced cranberries, apple juice, apple bits and allspice in a medium non-reactive sauce pan.
Bring to a boil, lower heat. Simmer uncovered 10 minutes.
Serve warm or chilled.
Best when made a day ahead.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add onion.
Add milk and egg, stirring lightly.

title: rum cake
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex dish with the Annisette biscuits (lay biscuits on side).
In a cereal bowl, put milk almost to top of dish and add 2 tablespoons rum flavoring.
Pour over biscuits.
Set aside.
Make vanilla pudding and let cool, then pour over biscuits.
Make chocolate pudding and let cool. Pour over vanilla pudding and refrigerate.
Before serving, put on Cool Whip, then slivered almonds.
Grate chocolate cookies over top.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Pam or grease Bundt pan.
Layer rolls evenly.
Add dry pudding mix and nuts.
Bring butter, sugar and cinnamon to a boil.
Pour over rolls; let stand overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: weatherman cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; let cool.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, flour and salt alternately with liquid.
Add vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Dribble chocolate chips and nuts over batter.
Bake for 40 minutes, or until done, in a 350° oven.
Cool, then sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: angel squares
directions: Mix the cake according to package directions.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients, excluding chicken, to make the sauce. Mix chicken and as much sauce as you like. Simmer and eat on bread or without. Good lunch.

title: china scallops
directions: Slice scallops crosswise into 1/4-inch thick disks.
Pare cucumber; cut lengthwise into 16 strips, then crosswise into fourths.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Cut and separate flowers.
Boil 5 minutes.
Drain and cool. Put flour in one bowl, beaten eggs in another bowl and breadcrumbs in another bowl.

title: tortilla soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the chicken and beef broth, onion, salsa and cumin over medium heat. Bring to a boil, then reduce the heat to low. Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Prepare chicken and vegetables; wash chicken and giblets under cold water.
Place in a large kettle with quartered onion, celery, parsley, 2 1/2 teaspoon salt, whole peppers, bay leaf and 2 cups water.
Bring to boiling and reduce heat; simmer, covered.
Simmer gently for 1 1/2 hours, or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from bones in large pieces; meat should measure 5 cups. Strain stock; measure and skim off fat.
Add water to make 4 cups, if necessary.
Cook carrots and potatoes in 4 cups stock, covered, for 20 minutes, or until tender.
Strain; liquid should measure 3 cups.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla together.
Gradually add flour, baking soda and salt to mixture. Stir in oats.
Add rest of ingredients one at a time.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove.
Cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: heavenly cream ambrosia
directions: Whip the heavy cream, then fold in the sour cream and orange liqueur.
Dice orange sections and grapefruit.
Fold into cream with coconut and marshmallows.
Chill overnight.
Garnish with sliced orange steeped in orange liqueur.
Serves 8.

title: italian garden medley
directions: Crumble and fry sausage lightly to remove grease.
Drain and set aside.
Cube zucchini. Cut peppers into squares after removing centers and seeds.
Cook zucchini and peppers in salt water until crisp-tender, about 6 minutes.
Drain.

title: gar's rolls
directions: Mix flour, salt, and shortening.
Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water, add egg.
Gradually add flour and beat well.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Knead on floured surface.
Roll dough 1/3 inch thick.
Cut with cutter.
Fold in half.
Let rise again at least 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 425° until brown, about 15 - 20 minutes.
Brush tops with margarine.
Makes about 36 rolls.

title: 40 punch rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add first salt and first flour. This makes an old fashioned cooking term - a sponge.
Let set for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Then add sugar, oil, eggs and last salt and flour. Mix and knead until velvety smooth.
Place in a large oiled bowl and let rise until double.
Cover tightly and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Mash sweet potatoes; add butter, brown sugar, milk, salt and rind.
With a tablespoon, scoop up 1/4 cup of mixture and shape around a marshmallow, using more potato as needed to make ball. Roll each ball in corn flakes.
Place on buttered baking sheet or dish; cover and freeze.
When ready to use, bake until marshmallows begin to ooze, about 20 minutes.
Makes 8 balls.

title: caramel and fruit fondue
directions: Melt together in double boiler until melted.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Serve with green apples.

title: italian coconut cream cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, oleo/butter, sugar and vanilla until well mixed.
Add nuts.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: hot chipped beef spread
directions: Mix all the ingredients together, except the walnuts.
Heat at 350° for 15 minutes, or in the microwave for 2 to 3 minutes, then top with walnuts.
This is great served with Wheat Thins or Triscuits or small pieces of toast.
Double this recipe for a large crowd.

title: cherry cheese spread
directions: Soften cheese and cut up cherries.
Beat cheese and cherries in small mixing bowl.
Add some cherry juice and beat until it is of a good spreading consistency.
Serve on saltines.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple, fruit cocktail and cherries. Dissolve gelatin in water.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour mixture into a medium size cake pan and freeze.
Cut into squares and place on lettuce leaves.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all in blender and beat on high for 1 minute or 2 minutes
by hand beater.
Pour into greased 10-inch pie pan. Bake 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: lo-fat granola
directions: Melt liquid items in large pan.
Mix in dry items except raisins.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Stir every 5 minutes while baking.
Add raisins after baking.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: I can substitute 2 egg whites or egg beaters for eggs.

title: fat free strawberry yum yum
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, Butter Buds and 1 cup of Grape Nuts together.
Spread into a long pan or glass dish.
Press down to make a crust.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef in strips and then in bite-size pieces.
Brown meat. Add soy sauce, garlic and ginger.
Cook until meat is tender, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Add vegetables except tomatoes.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add cornstarch and water.
Cook until thickened.
Add tomatoes and heat through.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients until creamy, then add remaining ingredients.
Form into small balls and pat down with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: copper pennies carrot salad
directions: Cut carrots and cook 10 minutes.
Drain.
Mix with all other ingredients well.
Will keep a long time in refrigerator.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat eggs until well blended. Add corn, milk, flour, sugar and salt. Mix well. Melt butter in a 12 x 7-inch baking dish. Pour in corn mixture; spoon butter over mixture. Bake for 50 minutes, or until brown on top and firm. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: okra gumbo
directions: Wash okra and cut crosswise in thin slices.
Peel and dice tomatoes.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Put okra, onions, green pepper and garlic into skillet with bacon drippings and cook until just tender.
Add tomatoes and cook slowly, covered, about 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle crumbled bacon over dish when ready to serve.
Good served over rice.

title: breakfast casserole(serves 10)
directions: Brown ground meat and drain.
Beat eggs separately.
Add all ingredients together in bowl.
Spray casserole dish, 9 x 14-inch, with Pam and pour in dish.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 3/4 to 1 hour, until brown.

title: funnel cakes
directions: Mix eggs and sugar; stir in milk.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until smooth.
Add flour.
Drop from funnel into a pan of lard or oil.
Fry until golden brown.

title: yabba-dabba-doo squares
directions: Microwave:
Melt margarine in large microwave bowl at High 45 seconds.
Add marshmallows; toss to coat.
Cook 1 minute or until marshmallows are smooth when stirred.
Add cereal; toss to coat well.
Press firmly into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 1 hour. Cut into squares.
Store in cool place.
Makes 24 squares.

title: brown rice
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Saute onion and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no guilt potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate several hours.
(May also add chopped egg.)
Before serving, add more dressing to moisten salad well.
Yields 2 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Combine all remaining ingredients with meat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: eloise's potatoes
directions: Fill 6-quart kettle almost full with potatoes and onions (sliced).
Cook until done, then pour off water.
Heat milk and butter; thicken with flour and add lots of cheese.
Pour over potatoes and stir.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes and brown in oven at 350° to 400°.

title: venison roast
directions: Place venison in bowl.
Cover with equal parts wine or vinegar and water.
Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours to 3 days, turning several times.
When ready to cook, remove meat from liquid and sear on all sides in hot fat.
Be careful to prevent sticking to the side of the pan!
Add 1 cup of the pickling liquid, cover and cook slowly about 3 hours.
Make a gravy from the drippings and add 3 to 4 ginger snaps.
Stir until smooth and add rest of the pickling mixture to gravy.

title: chocolate mousse(serves 6; under 300 calories)
directions: Combine chocolate pieces, boiling water, Angostura and egg yolks in blender.
Whirl until smooth.
Cool to room temperature. Beat egg whites in bowl until stiff.
Fold in chocolate mixture. Spoon mixture into serving dishes; chill for several hours.
Serve with demi-tasse.
Contains 265 calories per serving.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in large bowl; add melted butter, eggs, buttermilk, vanilla and 2/3 of the coconut. Mix well.
Pour mixture into shell. Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes or until set.

title: firecracker coleslaw salad
directions: Prepare the dressing; combine salt and garlic in large mixing bowl.
Mash to a paste with back of spoon.
Add the next 8 ingredients. Whisk until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients and toss to mix; let the slaw stand at least 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: turtles
directions: Mix caramel, butter and milk over medium heat.
Melt, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Cool.
Butter wax paper.
Lay a small amount of chopped pecans in little piles.
Dip 1 tablespoon of mixture over nuts and shape.
Place in freezer at least 1 hour. Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip nut mixtures in chocolate to coat.

title: sweet potato pineapple bake
directions: Mix potatoes, sugar, salt and flour.
Add eggs, butter and milk; beating well.
Add vanilla.
Mix pineapple in by hand. Blend well.
Grease casserole dish lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until set (bake longer if deep dish).

title: quick baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Stir and simmer over low heat, approximately 30 minutes, or bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a bowl.
Make a well and add in order, oil, egg yolks, water and vanilla.
Beat with spoon until smooth.

title: mexican luncheon
directions: Brown meat.
Add onion and green pepper.
Blend in salt, sugar and chili powder.
Stir in tomatoes, milk and sour cream.
Add uncooked macaroni and cover pan.
Cook 20 minutes on low heat. Top with grated cheese, if desired.

title: cajun's beef
directions: Brown meat in shortening, mashing often to avoid lumping.
Use a Dutch oven.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Bring to a slow boil; reduce heat to simmer, cover and cook about 40 minutes or longer.
Taste for seasonings.
Stir often to prevent sticking.

title: shrimp pilaf
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; save to use later.
Add bacon grease to water in which you cook rice.
In another pan, melt butter.
Add celery and bell pepper; cook a few minutes.
Add shrimp which have been sitting in Worcestershire sauce for at least an hour and have been dredged in flour.
Stir and simmer until flour and shrimp are cooked.
Add salt and pepper.
Now, add cooked rice; mix until rice is all "buttery" and "shrimpy."
You may need to add more butter.
Into this, crumble bacon over top and serve hot.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: In a bowl, cream butter with sugar, then add flour.
Spread in a baking pan.
Bake at 250° for one hour.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Combine cream cheese with milk, Lea & Perrins sauce, crab meat and green onions. Turn onto greased 8-inch pie plate and top with almonds. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Keep warm over a candle in a chafing dish.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten crescent rolls out in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool.

title: ruby punch
directions: Add sugar to boiling water, stir to dissolve.
Add fruit juices.
Chill. Add ginger ale when serving.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: royal cream pie
directions: Chop
nuts and press into pie crust.
Bake according to directions
until
light
brown.
Let cool.
Combine sugar and cream
cheese;
blend.
Add Cool Whip and blend.
Pour mixture into shell. Top with can of pie filling.
Chill until firm.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger and bacon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake in a casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candied apples
directions: Create a syrup of 2 cups sugar, 2/3 cup corn syrup and water. Add cinnamon candies for color and flavor.
Stir mixture until dissolved.
Boil and simmer, covered, for 3 minutes.
Uncover and cook to just under the hard crack stage.
Keep pan over warm water.

title: garlic sausage
directions: In a bowl or with a food processor, mix beef, garlic, 1 1/2 teaspoons paprika and remaining ingredients until well blended. Shape into smooth 10-inch long sausages.
Wrap, cover and refrigerate overnight.
Place sausage on rack in broiler pan. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, or until sausages are very firm and brown.
Sprinkle with remaining paprika.
Wrap airtight. Refrigerate up to 1 week or freeze up to 3 weeks.
To serve, cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Makes 2 slices, 32 slices each.

title: one of each casserole
directions: Using a paper towel, rub the butter around the inside of a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crumble the meat into the casserole dish.
Sprinkle rice and onion soup over meat.
Mix mushroom soup and water together in a small bowl.
Pour over rice mixture.
Cover tightly and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas scents
directions: Combine all together in a saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer as long as desired.
Add water if necessary. Store in refrigerator and use again.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix turkey or chicken with 1 cup rice (washed).
Add 1/2 cup onions, 1/2 cup peppers and seasoned salt.
Mix well.
Form in small balls.
Brown in 2-quart pan.
Add remaining washed rice, remaining onions, peppers and oregano.
Cover and simmer.
Let cook until the rice appears through the chicken balls.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of butter and add brown sugar.
Pour into bottom of Bundt pan.
Arrange nuts in bottom of pan if desired. Melt 1 stick of butter and add granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Dip frozen rolls into mixture and arrange in Bundt pan.
Pour remaining mixture over rolls.
Let rise 12 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cream caramels
directions: Sprinkle nuts on buttered 8-inch pan.
Mix in saucepan, all ingredients except last cup of cream.
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Then add the last cup cream.
Continue to stir mixture as it thickens and cook to 250° or until a hard ball is formed when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and pour over nuts in pan.
When cold, cut in squares and wrap in squares of wax paper.

title: baja-derves
directions: In a large bowl, combine cheese, chili peppers, olives, onion and mayonnaise or salad dressing.
Gently fold in shrimp.
Arrange about 20 tortilla chips on a 12-inch microwave-safe platter.

Top each chip with a rounded teaspoonful of the cheese mixture. Microcook, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 1 to 2 minutes (low wattage: place 12 chips on a paper plate and cook 1 to 2 minutes) or until cheese is melted, giving plate a half turn after 1 minute.
Repeat with remaining chips and cheese mixtures.
Makes 36 to 40 appetizer chips; 12 appetizer servings.

title: strawberry cheese cake
directions: Crust:
Melt oleo and add flour and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: aunt shirley's pizza soup(makes 4 servings)
directions: In saucepan, heat oil and stir-fry onions, green pepper and mushrooms until soft, not browned.
Add tomatoes (squished up a little so they are not whole, but bite sized chunks), beef broth, pepperoni and basil.
Cook until heated through.
Ladle into 4 ovenproof bowls.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Broil until cheese is bubbly or microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients and mix.
Pour mixture into uncooked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix rice and 1 beaten egg, 1/2 the cheese, salt and pepper. Place into a 9-inch pie plate, patting into place.
Mix spinach, milk, 2 eggs or 3 Egg Beaters eggs, mushrooms and cheese.
Pour over rice. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Mix with rest of ingredients.
Warm a few minutes and serve.

title: chocolate chip and mint brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Butter and flour 9-inch baking pan. Stir butter and unsweetened chocolate in heavy saucepan over low heat until melted and smooth.
Cool 15 minutes.
Add sugar, eggs and peppermint; whisk to blend.
Add flour and chocolate chips and blend well.
Pour batter into prepared pan, spreading evenly. Bake brownies until tester inserted into center comes out with moist crumbs attached, 25 minutes.
Cool brownies in pan on rack. Cut into squares and serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Heat water in a saucepan.
Add macaroni and salt.
Cook until macaroni is tender.
Drain macaroni and rinse with cold water. Add mayonnaise.
Dice onion, cucumber, green pepper and tomato in small pieces.
Add to macaroni.
Stir and chill.
Add more mayonnaise, if necessary.

title: spicy peach salad
directions: Drain peaches, reserving syrup.
Mash peaches.
Dissolve dry ingredients in boiling water.
Add peach syrup and vinegar.
Add pecans.
Mix well.
Whole maraschino cherries add color or garnish with canned crab apples, if desired.
Chill until firm.

title: gail's candy
directions: Crush together vanilla wafers and pecans.
Add condensed milk. Make in balls and roll in coconut and chill.

title: classic lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Stir in tomato juice, mushrooms, tomato paste, Worcestershire sauce and spices.
In 9 x 13-inch dish, layer noodles.
Cover with half of sauce and cheeses.
Repeat layer and cover with remaining sauce and cheeses.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove foil and bake 15 more minutes.
Garnish with parsley.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, chopped onion, Accent, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 to 3/4 of shredded ham.
Mix well. Roll into a ball and then roll ball onto shredded ham to cover. Refrigerate and serve with crackers.

title: cheesy cheddar potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Mix all ingredients; spoon into 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields approximately 6 servings.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cut chicken into pieces.
Cut tortillas into pieces or 1-inch squares.
Mix soups, milk and chilies.
Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Put 2 tablespoons chicken broth in it.
Layer tortillas and chicken soup mixture.
Top with cheese; cover with foil.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Combine egg, water and vinegar.
Blend with fork just until flour is all moistened.
Roll on plain flour.

title: peach jello
directions: Dissolve 1 package of Jell-O and 1 cup of boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Dissolve second package of Jell-O in remaining boiling water (1 cup).
Add ice cream and stir until melted and smooth.
Pour into serving bowl. Chill about 1 hour or until set, but not firm.
Arrange can peach slices on Jell-O, then ice cream mixture.
Top with the clear Jell-O.

title: grasshopper torte
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk in double boiler.
Cool.
Add flavoring and salt.
Chill.
Fold in whipped cream.
Cut cake in 3 layers.
Fill, frost and sprinkle with almonds.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and butter and press into a 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
In a medium bowl, combine eggs, 1 cup butter and powdered sugar.
Beat 10 to 15 minutes until smooth; spread over crust. Slice bananas over this, then crushed pineapple, then Cool Whip, then nuts.
Refrigerate 3 to 5 hours.

title: pumpkin raisin muffins
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients just until moist. Fill greased or paper-lined medium sized muffin cups (2/3 full). Sprinkle tops with cinnamon-sugar. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: plantain chips
directions: Cut off both ends and make a slit down the back (the length of the plantain) so you can peel the skin off.
If you have trouble peeling it, soak the whole plantain in warm salted water.
Slice the plantain thin (like potato chips).
Heat oil in large frying pan until hot.
Fry plantains until golden brown.
Salt to taste.

title: he man toll house cookies
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients. Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs and hot water.
Add dry ingredients. Mix well. Add nuts, chocolate bits and oatmeal.
Mix together thoroughly. Add vanilla. Bake 8 to 10 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with 2 cups hot water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Add enough cold water to juice to make 2 cups.
Add to jello.
Mix blueberries and pineapple with jello and congeal.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, sour cream, nuts and vanilla.
Spread over top of congealed mixture.

title: chipped beef with pecans
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and chipped dried beef.
Add onion to taste.
Place in a small baking dish and sprinkle nuts on top. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve with bread or crackers.
May be served cold in sandwiches.

title: jingle bell breakfast casserole
directions: Place croutons in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with cheese and mushrooms.
Spread cooked sausage and onion over cheese.
Beat eggs or egg substitute with 2 cups milk and seasonings; pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
The next day, mix soup with remaining 1/2 cup milk and spread on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash casserole 3
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a greased casserole. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: herb curry dip
directions: Blend all ingredients and chill.
Serve with vegetables, chips or crackers.

title: pop's popcorn balls
directions: Put sugar, brown sugar, syrup and water in a saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Add butter and continue cooking, without stirring, until the temperature is 240° or until mixture forms a soft ball when tested in cold water.
Put popped corn in a large bowl and sprinkle with salt.
Pour the hot syrup over it and mix thoroughly.
Shape into balls with gloved or buttered hands, so they don't burn.
Wrap in plastic wrap.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix soup as directed and pour over whole corn, mixing well. Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Cut tomatoes into quarters and place around the sides and bake for about 5 to 10 minutes longer.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 325° (45 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered).

title: party pita pockets
directions: Cut round pita bread in half to form pocket.
To each pocket add about 1 tablespoon of baked beans.
Spread along side (inside), 1 tablespoon of cottage cheese (spread over the beans), 3 or 4 onion slices, 3 or 4 cucumber slices.
Top with shredded lettuce or alfalfa sprouts.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Let cream cheese soften.
Mix the cream cheese, peanut butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Spoon mixture into pie shell.
Sprinkle with pecans on top, if desired.
Keep refrigerated.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Mix the cold water with the gelatine and boil. Add the remaining ingredients. Mix and set in the refrigerator; will set up.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Peel
potatoes,
slice and place in kettle.
Add water, cover and
boil
until tender.
Mash until free of lumps.
Add sugar, margarine
and pineapple;
stir well.
Place in casserole, cover with marshmallows.	Place in oven and bake at 350° and brown.

title: cabbage, potato and onion skillet
directions: Melt the butter in a 10-inch skillet and saute the cabbage, potatoes and onion until tender, about 7 to 10 minutes.
Pour cream into the skillet and season with a little salt and pepper, stirring to blend.
Cover the skillet and let simmer about 5 minutes.
This delicious, creamy mixture serves 4.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Make into balls.
(I use No. 24 dipper.)
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix rest of ingredients together, then simmer on top of stove.
Then pour over meat balls.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Do not cover while baking.

title: peppy parmesan potatoes
directions: Lightly grease 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Put potatoes in dish. Add onion, pepper, salt and cheese. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: potted venison
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Put first three ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Let stand overnight.
Drain and mix in cold water.
Drain again and put into large pot with remaining ingredients, stirring occasionally.
Cook 30 minutes or until desired consistency.
Pour into 6 to 8 hot sterilized pint jars and seal.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: chicken pacific
directions: Combine sour cream and seasonings.
Dip chicken in mixture. Roll in crumbs.
Bake in well-buttered pan at 350° for 1 hour or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: instant pudding chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugars, flavoring, pudding and eggs thoroughly. Mix flour and baking soda and add to mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot and spicy wings
directions: Cut off and discard tips of chicken wings.
Cut wings at joints to make 24 pieces.
Rinse pieces and pat dry.
Fry wing pieces, a few at a time, in deep hot oil for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown and no longer pink.
Drain on paper towels. Keep pieces warm in a 300° oven while frying remaining pieces. Transfer wings to serving dish.
In a saucepan melt margarine or butter.
Stir in hot pepper sauce.
Pour over wings, turning to coat.
For dipping sauce, in a small mixing bowl stir together sour cream, mayonnaise or salad dressing, basil, parsley, and milk.
Serve wings with dipping sauce.
Garnish with fresh basil, if desired.
Makes 8 to 12 appetizer servings.

title: baked chicken in aluminum foil
directions: Slice lemon, mushroom and onion.
Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper, parsley and wine.
Heat oven to 400°.
Place chicken on the aluminum foil.
Place mushroom, butter and onion over the chicken. Wrap chicken with foil.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or until chicken is done.

title: jumbo shells with cheese filling
directions: Prepare pasta as directed, cooking 9 minutes.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Arrange in single layer in greased roasting pan. Mix together cheeses, eggs, salt and pepper.
Fill shells with cheese mixture.
Pour sauce over shells and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle immediately with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute butter and onion.
Cook broccoli as on package; drain. Add garlic cheese to onion and butter, then cream of mushroom soup, then add cooked broccoli.

title: chutney and cheese
directions: Let cheese soften and pour 1/2 jar of chutney over it.
Serve with Hi-Ho or Ritz crackers.
Easy and very good!

title: seasoning mix
directions: Mix together.
Use this before barbecuing or smoking meat. Place on meat 1 hour before cooking.

title: vinegar cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch; set aside.
Bring vinegar and water to a boil.
Stir in sugar mixture and cook until thickened.
Pour mixture into crust-lined pie pan.
Place top crust on top and cut a few holes in it.
Bake until top crust is golden brown.

title: creamed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender; drain. Add butter, cream cheese and 1/3 cup milk or cream. Mix on low speed. Add remaining ingredients. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: aunt lee's tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Mix well.
Roll lightly on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness. Bake at 350°.

title: halibut in tarragon
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients; pour over the fish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until flakes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Add milk a little at a time.
Blend thoroughly and fold in Cool Whip by hand.
Put this mixture into graham cracker crust and freeze pie.
Remove from freezer one hour before serving.
If you double this recipe and use regular size pie crusts, you can make three pies.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and add boiling water last.
Pour into greased and floured 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Bake in the oven for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: beef and mushrooms over rice
directions: Saute mushrooms in small amount of vegetable oil; set aside. Brown meat; add 2 cups of wine and mushrooms.
Simmer 20 minutes. (Wine will cook down quickly.)
Add golden cream of mushroom soup and simmer for 20 more minutes.
(If too thick, add more wine.) Cook rice as directed on package.
Serve meat over rice.
Serves approximately 6 people.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix in stuffing mix.
Parboil squash; drain.
Mix squash with carrots, onions, sour cream and soup and 1/2 of stuffing.
Spread in a casserole dish; sprinkle remaining stuffing on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crush 2 packages crackers; mix with melted margarine.
Line casserole dish like a pie shell.
Layer chicken, soup mixture and 1 package crushed crackers in order, ending with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: new england muffins
directions: Place melted shortening in bowl.
Stir in sugar, eggs and milk.
Mix 4 dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Beat thoroughly.
Fill greased muffin pans (1/2 full).
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: blueberry congealed salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O according to package.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Chill until set.

title: salmon stew
directions: Fry bacon, reserving drippings.
Place onion and potatoes in pot; boil until tender, about 10 minutes.
Add salmon, ketchup, bacon drippings, salt, pepper and hot sauce to potatoes and onion. Cover with water; cook 10 to 15 minutes or until thick.

title: cool whip frosting
directions: Stir together chopped pecans and 1/4 cup melted butter. Spread in an even layer in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until pecans are toasted. Remove from oven and let cool. Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until light and fluffy. Stir in pecans and vanilla.

title: chicken in a skillet
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil and brown chicken.
Drain well. Add onion soup mix blended with the water and tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour until well blended.
Chop tomatoes and add to flour mixture.
Cook until thick.
Season with salt, pepper and sugar.
Gradually add hot milk; cook and stir until boiling point is reached.
Remove from heat.
Good served over rice.

title: bernice's carrot cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil and mix well.
Add eggs and vanilla next; blend thoroughly.
Add carrots and nuts last. Batter is enough for a 13 x 9-inch pan or three 8-inch pans.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
May or may not need frosting; it's your choice.

title: frozen dessert salad(serves 6)
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients, except greens.
Pour into refrigerator tray or pan.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares and arrange on greens.
Serve with dressing of your choice.

title: pralines
directions: Mix soda and buttermilk and dissolve sugar.
Use large saucepan and boil slowly to soft ball stage.
Mixture turns brown as it cooks.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add flavoring, margarine and pecans.
Stir until it begins to look like it is ready to sugar or cream.
Drop in small cakes on wax paper.

title: shortbread chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, margarine, both sugars and the eggs until creamy.
Add vanilla, soda, salt and mix well.
Add flour.
Blend and stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonful on ungreased cookie sheet, bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix the soup, salad oil, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and dried mustard together.
Pour the mixture over the cooked carrots, onion and celery.
Chill overnight.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add onions and celery and simmer until tender.
Add broccoli spears, rice,
soups and cheese.
Mix well.

title: nutty spinach dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients.
Be sure to thaw frozen spinach.
Cover, refrigerate until serving at least 2 hours.
Garnish with additional chopped nuts.
Serve with fresh vegetables for dipping or use as a filling for fresh mushroom caps.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: green goddess salmon salad
directions: Drain salmon.
Combine with cucumber and green pepper. Arrange avocado halves on 4 small plates lined with salad greens. Spoon in salmon mix; garnish with tomato slices and olives.
Serve with dressing.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter.
Set aside.
Cook butter and flour over medium heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the half and half, slowly, stirring with a whisk.
Add chicken stock and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add broccoli, carrots and onions.
Cook over low heat about 20 to 25 minutes or until flavors have blended and carrots are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add heavy cream and nutmeg just before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: oreo ice cream pie
directions: Crush cookies, reserve 2/3 cup for top.
Mix crumbs, 1/4 cup margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Melt chocolate, 1/2 cup margarine, sugar, salt and milk.
Boil 4 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Spread over crust.
Chill until set. Spread ice cream and sprinkle with crumbs.

title: beet salad
directions: Drain beets, measure juice.
Add water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Bring to boil.
Remove from heat, add jello, sugar, vinegar and horseradish.
Stir until gelatin and sugar have dissolved.
Cool partially.
Add beets, celery and onion and put into mold.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip.
Add dry jello and mix well.
Add fruit.
Mix and pour into crust.
Place in refrigerator for 1 hour before serving.

title: low calorie lunch
directions: Bake or microwave potato.
Top with cottage cheese and salsa. Serve with celery and carrot sticks.

title: euvonne's cracky bars
directions: Sift together the flour, salt and soda; set aside.
In mixing bowl, blend the shortening, sugar and eggs; beat well.
Combine milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Remove 1/3 of batter to another bowl.
Add nuts and melted chocolate.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange whole graham crackers in single layers over batter in pan. To remaining batter in mixing bowl, add the chocolate chips. Drop by spoonfuls over crackers.
Spread to cover.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and let sit for 20 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients and then add oats.

title: garden stroganoff
directions: Place broccoli and carrots in a steamer basket.
Cover and steam over 1-inch boiling water for 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain and set aside.
In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; saute until onion is tender, about 2 minutes.
Stir in flour and blend until smooth. Gradually add milk; cook, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sour cream, Parmesan cheese and mustard.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Serve over hot noodles.
Makes 4 servings.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Stir milk, sugar and shortening until dissolved. Cool.
Add yeast dissolved in water and enough flour to make a batter. Beat until smooth and let rise until double.
Add baking powder, baking soda, salt and enough flour to make dough.
Knead a few minutes. Roll out.
Cut enough for meal.
Let rise until double.
Store remainder covered in refrigerator.
Use as needed.

title: teriyaki glazed chicken
directions: Remove skin, bake at 425° for 1/2 hour; drain fat.
Mix all remaining ingredients; pour over chicken, turning once.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: cherry treasure mold
directions: In mixer bowl, beat together cream cheese and mayonnaise. Dissolve jello in boiling water and stir into cream cheese mixture.
Mix in ginger ale and refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a shallow 8-cup mold.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: pierogi
directions: Cook potatoes.
Drain.
Add cheese.
Saute onion in margarine. Add to potatoes and mash.
Let cool.

title: green pea casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, put a layer of peas and a layer of asparagus, then add cheese and pour on mushroom soup.
Sprinkle some cheese and put pats of butter on top.
Place in oven at 350° until hot through.

title: oven swiss steak
directions: Cut meat into 6 serving-size portions. Combine flour and salt; with meat mallet, pound 2 tablespoons of the mixture into meat on both sides. Brown meat on both sides in hot shortening. Transfer meat to a 12 x 7-inch baking dish. Blend remaining 2 tablespoons flour mixture into pan drippings. Stir in undrained tomatoes, celery, carrot and Worcestershire sauce. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly; pour over meat. Bake steak, covered, in a 350 degree oven about 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown ground beef with onions and green peppers.
Drain grease and add green beans, tomato sauce, ketchup, salt and pepper (to taste).
Press crescent rolls into 9-inch pie pan to form crust. Mix egg and 1 cup Mozzarella cheese.
Spread on bottom of crust. Add meat mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes or until crust is golden.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Chop up garlic and parsley.
Brown garlic and parsley in olive oil.
When it starts to brown, add one can of clams, 3/4 bottle of clam juice and some black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Shut off gas and add to cooked spaghetti.

title: low calorie eggnog
directions: Combine Better 'N Eggs and milk in mixing bowl or blender. Add remaining ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes or until well blended.
Refrigerate until ready to use.
Has 0 g fat and 50 calories.

title: chicken noodle casserole
directions: Prepare egg noodles according to package directions. I cook mine in the chicken broth. In a large skillet, cook celery, bell pepper and onion in butter until tender, but not brown. Stir in soup, milk, cheese, salt and pepper and 3/4 cup chicken broth. Stir until cheese melts. Add noodles and chicken. Pour into a greased 3-quart casserole dish. Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: coconut milk tart
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease medium sized pie dish.
Beat ingredients together, mixing well.
Pour into pie dish.
Bake for approximately 1 hour until golden brown.
Serve when cool with fresh cream.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: *Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add melted butter.
Put 2/3 of this mixture on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: delicious red beet eggs
directions: Drain beets, reserving liquid.
Pour liquid into a glass bowl; simmer sugar, vinegar, salt and spices until sugar dissolves.
Mix with beet juice.
Add beets, eggs and onion. Cover and chill at least 2 hours, preferably longer.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef with milk and cracker crumbs in bowl. Season with salt and pepper. Shape into 1 1/2-inch meatballs. Place in 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Combine vinegar, catsup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, onion and green pepper in saucepan. Bring to a boil; pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix almonds and cracker crumbs.
Have 2 cups.
Add rest of ingredients.
Place in casserole, greased or sprayed with Pam. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry dump cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan or larger.
Mix pineapple and cherries in baking pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top of pineapple and cherries.
Then sprinkle chopped nuts over dry cake mix.
Then add pats of margarine over that.
This will brown.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Lightly grease casserole.
Mix all ingredients except chicken and soup mix.
Put in casserole pan.
Place chicken on top of mixture.
Sprinkle chicken with onion soup mix and seal with foil. Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peek!!

title: tamale pie
directions: Cook meat and drain.
Cook pepper, onion and garlic in large nonstick skillet until tender.
Add meat, tomato sauce and seasoning (only 1/2 teaspoon salt).
Cook 5 minutes, set aside.

title: indiana corn pudding
directions: Mix well all ingredients. Pour into 9 x 13 buttered baking dish. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°. Meal will rise in this and looks like cornbread.

title: chipped beef appetizers
directions: Cream the cheese. Add enough mayonnaise to make it smooth and easy to spread.
Mix together thoroughly.
Have butcher slice chipped beef thick enough to spread cheese mixture on.
Spread mixture thinly on meat slices. Roll up like jelly roll.
Cut in 1-inch slices and fasten with toothpicks.

title: poppy seed dressing ham sandwiches
directions: Slice dinner rolls in half.
Put ham and cheese on slices of one side of the bread.
Heat margarine, mustard, poppy seed, onion, and worcestershire sauce together.
Spread mixture on other side of bread.
Put other side of bread on ham and cheese. Heat in oven at 350° for 10 - 15 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Lightly butter bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread coconut and nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions and pour into pan.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Mix avocados with lemon juice, salt and pepper (to taste). Set aside.
Mix taco mix, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Set aside.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
